1.name: Nue
1.description:
"Hah! You're leaving yourself wide open!"
A spirit combining the powers of a monkey, tanuki, tiger, and snake. These animal powers give her incredible physical abilities, so she doesn't need any weapons. Instead, she pulverizes her opponents with classical martial arts skills, preferring to win by knock out. Her only flaw is that she gets hungry really quickly, and then doesn't feel like fighting anymore.

skill.name: Summon Fanged Beast
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun.

abilities.name: Beast Factor
abilities.description: Increases 15% of Crit Rate.

abilities.name: Magical Beast Factor
abilities.description: Increases 50% of Crit DMG.

2.name: Joan of Arc
2.description:
"I will build and protect a future for everyone."
A soldier who captured the hearts of a generation with her charisma and mystique. Perhaps because of her heroic yet untimely death she developed a bit of a sarcastic streak as a spirit, and she tends to poke fun at people. But now that the heresy has been cleared from her name, she's giving her cynical side a rest. Instead she just feels deep pride over being the first national beauty of France.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: Holy Knight's Oath
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Maiden's Prayer
abilities.description: All Divina team members deal 5% more DMG.

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

3.name: Shishiou
3.description:
"Alright, who's next?"
The spirit of a dignified sword. The aura she emanates can stop any ordinary spirit dead in its tracks if they come too close, and with a few harsh words, she can scare away lowly beasts. Actually, stories about her have gotten so blown out of proportion, that when she goes out walking by herself people call her "Mad Dog." But she doesn't understand why, since lions are in the cat family...

skill.name: Howling Grand Slash
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to further enemies.

abilities.name: Shishi's Pride
abilities.description: Increases 5% of DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

4.name: Mjölnir
4.description:
"BOOM! BOOM!"
The spirit of a hammer from Norse mythology. People say her big bust is also like a "red hot hammer," and in a sense it does have incredible destructive power. Well, maybe they're more like spheres than hammers... But still, perhaps because of that destructive power, she is often found amid scrap heaps and junkyards. She may not show it publicly, but in fact she has had some terribly difficult times living in poverty. That's why she's so stingy. But, since she's also scatterbrained, she loses her purse a lot.
[Special Bond] Increases DMG dealt by Chidori.

skill.name: Lightning Hammer
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Persistent Fighter
abilities.description: Reduces 90% of DMG taken when near death.

abilities.name: Mass Destruction
abilities.description: Increases 20% of skill DMG.

She may not show it publicly, but in fact she has had some terribly difficult times living in poverty. That's why she's so stingy. But, since she's also scatterbrained, she loses her purse a lot.
[Special Bond] Increases DMG dealt by Chidori.

5.name: Adramelech
5.description:
"Burn, my sweet sword!"
A spirit worshipped as the sun god. He holds a sword in his right hand while sinister magic swirls around his left. You could say he's a magic swordsman. He always ranks at the top of the list of the World's Richest Spirits, and his bank account is enough to overturn heaven and earth. That's why he doesn't have much faith in other people -- he's always surrounded by spirits who are after his money.

skill.name: Magic Bullet Storm
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 3 enemies (melee priority).

abilities.name: Sun God
abilities.description: Skill attacks have 40% chances of inflicting Burn.

6.name: Momotaro
6.description:
"Gather, comrades. There is someone we must defeat!"
The legendary demon-fighting warrior accompanied by a dog, monkey and pheasant. He wasn't the best in terms of swordsmanship or other fighting abilities, but his innate bravery, endless care for his friends, and visionary leadership enabled him to achieve his goals. Now, after much, much training and practice he has finally managed to become a top-class fighter.

skill.name: Cry of the Gods
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

abilities.name: Child of God
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG dealt by Divina team members when this daemon is Team Leader.

7.name: Lady Nō
7.description:
"Leering at me again? You should be ashamed of yourself!"
The daughter of Saito Dosan, she was the wife of Oda Nobunaga. She doesn't like feeling constrained, so she's always loosening her obi to expose her front side. It basically looks like she's naked if you look at her directly. Yet, strangely enough, no one has ever testified to having seen her naked. Maybe it has some kind of indescribable power...

skill.name: Alluring Dance
skill.description: Reduces the DEF of 2 enemies (melee priority) by {delay1} for a limited time.

8.name: Hraesvelgr
8.description:
"Yum! Oh my gosh, this is good!"
The spirit of a giant from Norse mythology. She loves food and appreciates delicious things no matter where they are from. When she has to go somewhere far away she turns into an eagle and enjoys her journey from the skies. The only catch is that since she's a giant, she has to eat a lot of food to feel full. So restaurants sometimes ban her from coming there again. Lately her favorite shop is a place in the Far East called "THE JOHN"(it has a weird name because the owner is bad at English).

skill.name: The Big Bite
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to surrounding enemies.

9.name: R'lyeh
9.description:
"Hmm, yes, I can see it now. The continent hidden beneath the sea..."
The forbidden book of the Cthulhu Mythos. It supposedly contains lots of secrets, legends and symbols, but her memory is bad so you can't get many facts out of her. She has been a spirit for quite some time now, and has friends and fans worldwide.

skill.name: Doorway to Demons
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority).

abilities.name: Nightmare Binding
abilities.description: Skill attacks have 65% chances of inflicting Sleep.

10.name: Tennyo Ayame
10.description:
"Doing laundry feels so GOOD!"
A spirit who lives in heaven. There are actually all kinds of people in heaven, including totally average people, and she is one of the average ones. She will make you feel right at home and lead you to believe that the only difference between heaven and earth is the address. But actually, her spirit essence is far greater than any human's, and so is her strength in battle.

skill.name: Special Cooking
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to all allies. Targets receive {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

11.name: Tenjin
11.description:
"I'll put a curse on you even if you run to the ends of the earth!"
A spirit who controls the deep and sharply negative feelings of humanity, including but not limited to violent anger, vague resentment and general ill-will. They say Sugawara no Michizane is the one who gave him a reason to be reborn as A spirit. That's also why he wears a kimono. He looks gloomy and has a negative attitude all year round.

skill.name: Indignation
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

12.name: Lightning
12.description:
"Can you see how fast this is?"
The spirit of a double-action revolver. His birth story is complicated, but let's just say he wasn't very blessed. He stepped out of the public eye, living with outlaws and making shady behind-the-scenes deals. He is very serious at his core.

skill.name: Crotch Shot
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the lowest HP.

13.name: Okita Soji
13.description:
"I'm a man, okay? Get it right or pay the price!"
The spirit of the captain of the first unit of the Shinsengumi. He died suddenly of natural causes, so he seems to have left behind a lot of regrets. As a result he tends to immediately notice and point out negative things. In winter he always catches whatever sickness is going around and sleeps a lot, so he and everyone who knows him acknowledge that he doesn't reach his true potential. He is sometimes bewildered at his own form. since it is a representation of how people imagine him to be.

skill.name: Godspeed Level 3
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun.

abilities.name: Miracle Knight
abilities.description: Reduces 15% of DMG taken.

14.name: Ibaraki Doji
14.description:
"Hey, you're really cute!"
The right hand man of Shuten Doji. He is super friendly and has no dignity, in a good way. He's also known as a playboy who is constantly going after girls, which surprisingly doesn't seem to bother most people. So he has lots of connections, which might explain why he's so well liked in the first place. Deep down inside he's honest and hardworking.

skill.name: Demon Claw
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

abilities.name: Royal Demon
abilities.description: Increases 15% of Crit Rate.

15.name: Muramasa
15.description:
"S-so hungry tonight... Need food..."
The spirit of a sword that is considered as the demon sword. By some mistake most of the legends about her have to do with being unlucky. She never wanted it to be like this... But since that is what everyone expects of her, she uses some kind of quasi-hypnotism to make herself into the demon sword she was meant to be. Apparently she has monster DNA in her.

skill.name: Strange Invocation
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority).

abilities.name: Best Thing on Earth
abilities.description: Increases 15% of DMG dealt.

16.name: Shuten Doji
16.description:
"I am the King, so I make the Laws."
A king who built a castle on Mount Oe and controls all the demons across Japan. He originally never intended to settle down. It's just that he made a deal with Mikado and decided to come down to the human world. Ever since then he's been living at the Bureau of the Occult with Mikado. His motto is "lively and clear," and he's a nice guy, really manly. That's why so many demons have faith in him as they live their lives running free. He's also a little on the fancy side, writing poems in his spare time.

skill.name: Song of Karmic Downfall
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority), with a {probability} of inflicting Weak Poison.

17.name: Emperor Sutoku
17.description:
"One man's strength is another's fear."
A spirit known as the leading supernatural spirit in Japan. It all started with a tragedy when he was still alive. These days not many people go out of their way to try to understand him, so he keeps fighting, all alone. His elite lineage, combined with the explosive bursts of spirit essence granted him by his sublimated anger, make him quite powerful. Then again, maybe these rare powers have something to do with his constant loneliness.

skill.name: Anti-Curse Resonance
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Silence.

abilities.name: Heavenly Lineage
abilities.description: Increases 5% of DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

18.name: Princess Saho
18.description:
"Oh, a warm spring day would be so nice..."
The spirit of Mount Saho, which lies to the east of the ancient capital, Nara. The daughter of a good family that rules spring, and very close with Princess Tatsuta. They are eternal rivals, constantly vying to become more popular than the other. Actually, they perform as an underground idol duo, too. But this is a well-kept secret, and even the Bureau of the Occult doesn't officially recognize it. Lots of people are secretly fans, though. Their music is pretty loud, and she is in charge of vocals and shouting.
[Special Bond] Increases Princess Tatsuta's speed.

skill.name: Idol Hands
skill.description: Increases DMG dealt by 3 allies (ranged priority) by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Superstar
abilities.description: Increases own level by 10 when Princess Tatsuta is on the team.

19.name: Princess Tatsuta
19.description:
"Oh, a clear autumn day is so nice!"
The spirit of Mount Tatsuta, which lies to the west of the ancient capital, Nara. The daughter of a good family that rules fall, and very close with Princess Saho. They are eternal rivals, constantly vying to become the more popular one. Actually, they perform as an underground idol duo, too. But this is a well-kept secret, and even the Bureau of the Occult doesn't officially recognize it. Lots of people are secretly fans, though. Their music is pretty loud, and she is in charge of choruses, guitar and manipulation.
[Special Bond] Increases Princess Saho's speed.

skill.name: Wicked Idol of the West
skill.description: Increases all allies' DEF by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Superstar
abilities.description: Increases own level by 10 when Princess Saho is on the team.

20.name: Meito Kotetsu
20.description:
"You got anything I can cut?"
The spirit of what some say is the finest sword ever made. Whenever he gets excited he tends to start randomly cutting things. Even if it's Christmas Eve, once his adrenaline gets going he just loses himself and starts slashing through everything in the Bureau of the Occult -- the walls, the ceiling, desks, everything. He's built up a big tab for all the things he's destroyed, so he's not in a position to stand up against Mikado. He works with them as best he can, and uses the payment from the Bureau of the Occult to pay off his debt.

skill.name: Cut Up
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

21.name: Elaphure
21.description:
"Just what do you think I am?"
She may resemble something else, but don't be so fast to judge a book by its cover. A strange spirit who looks like an animal but isn't. She's the incarnation of a dragon. When she has spare time, she likes to fly around in the air looking for men she likes. But when she finds one she doesn't do anything. She just watches him.

skill.name: Storm Dragon Transformation
skill.description: Restores {value} HP; increases DEF by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Blood of Legend
abilities.description: Restores 2% of HP every 5 seconds.

22.name: Kintaro
22.description:
"You mean there is someone stronger than me?"
A great hero known as one of the Four Heavenly Kings of Raiko who saved the capital from evil. The spirit's trademark is his height. His reputation comes from his superhuman strength. He can wield a hundred class war axe with one hand. He was an orphan and grew up in the woods with animals. But his former home is now all gone, and his friends have migrated to other places.

skill.name: Great Blade of Magic
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to surrounding enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun to targets.

abilities.name: Four Heavenly Kings of Raiko
abilities.description: Increases 15% of DMG dealt when one of the Four Heavenly Kings of Raiko is on the team.

23.name: Diaochan
23.description:
"We must always be prepared for the worst, yes?"
A spirit who charms men and leads them around like puppies. A master of the dark arts. She acts all innocent but behind the scenes she does some nasty stuff. She doesn't think twice about ruining the life of a guy who falls for her. There seems to be a reason why she keeps doing such horrible things... The darkness in her heart runs deep.

skill.name: Temptation
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 2 enemies with the highest ATK. Targets deal {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

24.name: Chimera
24.description:
"Three beasts, one body! That's me, Chimera! Yea!"
The spirit of a high school girl with beast strength in both hands. She forgot her real name, but everyone calls her Chimera because of the way she looks. She's surprisingly cunning, and once she finds someone's weak spot she really likes to jab them there. People say she's like an evil snake in that way. She's really nice to kids, though, and popular with them, too. She's always putting on original improvisational comedy shows with them.
[Special Bond] Increases crit rate of Cerberus.

skill.name: Tragic Pattern
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (melee priority).

abilities.name: Three Beasts, One Body
abilities.description: Increases 15% of Crit Rate when Cerberus and Hydra are on the team.

25.name: Daji
25.description:
"So fun, school is just so fun..."
A spirit of the most evil woman in all of history. She ruined the largest country in East Asia using her looks and wits as her only weapons. Her true form is a huge spirit, but nothing is known beyond that. With the enormous spirit essences under her control she can turn into human form and slip into human society. But these days she adjusted her looks a bit and is apparently living as a high school student. The catch is that in human form she can only use her spirit essence for a few minutes at a time.

skill.name: Evil and Ash
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 2 enemies with the least HP. Targets take {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

26.name: Flying Nimbus
26.description:
"Here we go, wooo!"
The spirit of a magic flying cloud. She loves people with inner beauty, strength, and pure dreams, and tries to form partnerships with them. In something like a sponsorship contract, she agrees to help them with transportation if they outwardly appeal to her as a partner. The only problem is that she's booked solid and can't take on any new partnerships for the next few years.
[Special Bond] Increases Sun Wukong's skill DMG

skill.name: High-Speed Wave
skill.description: Restores {value} HP for 2 allies (melee priority); increases targets' speed by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Supersonic Aviation
abilities.description: Increases 15% of ATK speed to all melee allies.

[Special Bond] Increases Sun Wukong's skill DMG

27.name: Arondight
27.description:
"I will stand by my master!"
The spirit of a sword that aided a knight of the Round Table. Her backstory is questionable since she got a bad rap for killing an ally. But she doesn't have any regrets about it. He was simply carrying out his duties and she aided him as a tool, no more, no less. There are a number of issues preventing her from being reunited with the knight who used to be her owner.

skill.name: Liberated Sword
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to surrounding enemies; reduces targets' DEF by {delay1} for a limited time.

28.name: Yoichi's Bow
28.description:
"I can see you, no matter how far you run!"
The spirit of the favorite bow of Nasu no Yoichi, a samurai famous for his archery skills. Yoichi was indeed a genius, but actually the bow has an auto-targeting function by which it predicts the movements of the target and fires on its own. With this pretty much anyone can become a "genius," so she is really popular.

skill.name: Arrow of Light
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the highest ATK.

29.name: Zashiki Bokko
29.description:
"...Y-you can see me?!"
A spirit who lives quietly in Japanese homes. She's not hardworking or good at getting along with others, so she tends to be stiff and formal. She's not good at getting jokes either, which has earned her the title of "Joke Killer." Having a Zashiki Bokko around is actually a bigger deal than you might think. For example, last year a restaurant that used to be Deadsville reached three star status for a short time thanks to a Zashiki Bokko.

skill.name: Surge of Peacefulness
skill.description: Inflicts Sleep on an enemy (healers priority) for a limited time.

30.name: Peony the Ninja
30.description:
"Quiet, or I'll kill you!"
The spirit of a female ninja. Employer unknown. She takes great pride in being a ninja, but there isn't really anything noteworthy about her -- which in itself is noteworthy, according to some.

skill.name: Secret Ninja Skillbook
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to a random enemy.

31.name: Nickel Elf
31.description:
"Yawn... What? More practice? Sheesh!"
The spirit of elves that originate from the element nickel. They learned by watching humans to make a dance team. It's called ELF 118. There are a lot of members, and they're not all that great, but they're starting to spread by word of mouth on the streets.

skill.name: Vitality Dance
skill.description: Increases DMG dealt by a random ally by {delay1} for a limited time.

32.name: Yashichi
32.description:
"Another day, another fight. Who will I face today?"
The spirit of a common foot soldier who once served under a military commander. He is very skilled, but he chose not to become a famous warrior. He loves the battlefield and the stinging joy of being on the front lines. He's really famous for this among his fellow soldiers, and other armies fearfully refer to him as "Yashichi the Tiger." No one knows much about him beyond that.
[Special Bond] Increases Commander Yashichi's skill DMG

skill.name: Wave After Wave
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

"Another day, another fight. Who will I face today?"

No one knows much about him beyond that.
[Special Bond] Increases Commander Yashichi's skill DMG

33.name: Yatagarasu
33.description:
"Who are you calling a tour guide?! Show some respect!"
A spirit who makes a living showing the gods around. It used to be considered a sacred and sublime line of work, but, as in the human world, many things have changed over time in the spirit world, too, and giving tours isn't so easy any more. She puts a lot of effort into memorizing the best sightseeing spots and famous local products.

skill.name: Giant Crow Call
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to surrounding enemies.

34.name: Goblonara
34.description:
"Hah, I see ya over there! Lookin' stupid!"
The spirit of the so-called Queen among small fries, the goblin. Her job is basically to cause trouble. When other spirits pass by (it's the best if they are in a horse and buggy), they come out waving their clubs and attack, steal all the gold and valuables, and then retreat. There is nothing scarier for a merchant, but for a competent soldier they are a good way to earn some money.
[Special Bond] Increases DMG dealt by Gobrute.

skill.name: Plunder
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun.

35.name: Cleaver
35.description:
"Heh, heh... No need to be afraid."
The spirit of a knife made to cut through thick things. Both a wandering chef and an assassin, her dishes have a unique and unusual taste... At least, it would be interesting if that were true. Actually, she is neither a chef nor an assassin.

skill.name: Strike and Slice
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

36.name: Fire Mouse
36.description:
"A nice hot bath is the best..."
The spirit of a monster said to roam about the land. He has a strong affinity for fire, and the long hair flowing from his body is like licks of flame. He likes beauty and he LOVES hot baths. But you have to be careful if you take a bath after him, because he prefers for the water to be almost literally boiling, around 176 degrees Fahrenheit.

skill.name: Burst of Flames
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

37.name: Butterfly Knife
37.description:
"Are you sure you wanna do this? Your legs are shaking..."
The spirit of a knife that can flip and fold. Quick-witted and acrobatic. She's good at this one move where she flips around to mess with the enemy's eyes and then jumps in and attacks right where they least expect it. She used to be a gymnast.

skill.name: Limb From Limb
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the highest ATK.

38.name: Magic Mallet
38.description:
"One, two, here we go! And another one!"
The more you wave it around, the more things come flying out of this biscuit-looking spirit. It was originally created and used by a demon, but that was a little too violent for her, so she ran away. Ever since she met a certain person on the road, they have been traveling around together.

skill.name: Descent into Happiness
skill.description: Increases the Crit Rate of 2 allies (melee priority) by {delay1} for a limited time.

39.name: Lady Chacha
39.description:
"Alright, comrades! Follow my lead!"
The niece of Oda Nobunaga. A skilled orator with the gift of gab, whose distinctive timbre possesses a devilishly beguiling allure. As skilled at intimidating enemies as she is at inspiring feats of courage in others, she boasts a long line of ardent followers who hang on (or are controlled by?) her every word.

skill.name: Rousing Rhetoric Energy
skill.description: Increases DMG dealt by 2 allies (ranged priority) by {delay1} for a limited time.

40.name: Nurarihyon
40.description:
"Wot's that, eh?! You startin'?!"
A fierce little number who's used to ruling the roost. She might look small, but there's nothing diminutive about this lairy lass. Quick to jump into action when her pals get into scrapes, she's widely admired by her spirited chums. Unfortunately, she can be a tad testy when tempted, and has been known to shower those she's sweet on with insults instead of kisses.

skill.name: Minion March
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies; decreases targets' speed by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Ghoulish Guv'nor
abilities.description: Increases 5% of max HP of Phantasma team members.

41.name: Beelzebub
41.description:
"Hehe... D'ya want to see me get angry?"
Demonic leader of all things dastardly and diabolical. She sets to quaking the boots of even the most hardened of hellish heroes, and rules the underworld with an iron fist. Word has it her rather..."unique" body odor is a bit of a sore point—any known to have asked about it vanish quicker than you can say "deodorant deficit."

skill.name: Soaring Skull
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority).

abilities.name: Hallowed Master
abilities.description: Increases 30% of DMG dealt when this daemon is Team Leader.

42.name: Kogitsunemaru
42.description:
"One forged sword, comin' right up!"
An Anima with a voracious appetite for deep-fried tofu. This sword-tempering master's work includes some of the finest blades known to man or spirit. She's also famed for her sharp tongue, and is a hit among fellow spirits for her witty comebacks. In fact, her only weakness is her utter inability to resist deep-fried tofu, which she guzzles down with a gusto bordering on manic.

skill.name: Vexing Vixen
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the row of enemies directly in front.

abilities.name: Fox's Blessing
abilities.description: Reduces 25% of DMG taken.

43.name: Kintaro's Axe
43.description:
"Back in the woods, eh? Those were the good ol' days..."
The Anima of Kintaro's legendary trusty battleaxe. After years at Kintaro's side through thick and thin, the two developed an almost brotherly bond. They don't seem to spend as much time together as they used to, but you know what they say—once a BFF...
[Special Bond] Increases DMG dealt by Kintaro.

skill.name: Here Cometh The Thunder God
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to surrounding enemies.

abilities.name: Tempestuous Talisman
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG dealt.

44.name: Lü Lingqi
44.description:
"At-choo! Oh, poor me... ANOTHER cold?"
Daughter of Lü Bu, the most formidable and feared commander of China's Three Kingdoms period. Used to being treated with reverence on account of her lofty lineage, she longs for the warmth of a close human connection. Of late, she's taken to feigning sickness to lower herself in others' eyes, but she lacks the acting chops to pull it off.

skill.name: Legendary Lineage
skill.description: Restores {value} HP.

45.name: Isis
45.description:
"Hm? I spy with my little eye... something approaching from afar."
An ancient goddess who presides over the Nile's fertile banks. She's adored as a mother-figure among spirits for her kindness and silky-soft compassion. Her talents include a keen and penetrating insight, which she uses to deliver expert advice to those in a spot of bother.

skill.name: Heavenly Mother
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to all allies.

46.name: Ox Demon
46.description:
"Whatcha starin' at? You lookin' to get gobbled up?"
This pesky spirit is notorious for pestering people out for strolls along the beach. Ever since taking her brand of nuisance abroad, her antics have become infamous the world over. She sprays poison when she sneezes, so make sure to hide the pepper when she's around.

skill.name: Hell Render
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (melee priority), with a {probability} of inflicting Poison.

abilities.name: Poison Sneeze
abilities.description: Increases 15% of skill DMG.

47.name: Spider's Thread
47.description:
Oh, go on then... But this is your last chance!"
A merciful spirit given to taking pity on even the least deserving of souls. Her attention span is short, however, and she's been known to give short shrift to potential benefactors when not "in the mood." All things considered, you're far more likely to get an earful of abuse from her than an extra chance. But hey, such is life, right? That's what she says, at least.

skill.name: Zero Chance
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies. Targets take {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Last Chance
abilities.description: 32% chances of inflicting Sleep on all ranged foes at the start of each wave.

48.name: Azure Sword
48.description:
"Come, stain my sword with your blood!"
A brilliant blue blade coveted by many, and no stranger to victory on the battlefield. His military record has seen him recommended for various positions of authority, but he declines each time, claiming to prefer the raw thrill of the frontlines.

skill.name: Slice of Life
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

49.name: Koropokkur
49.description:
"Make fun of my size, will ya!"
A pint-sized spirit from the northern provinces. Feisty with a capital "F," he hunts opponents twice his size camouflaging himself in burdock leaves to get the jump on prey. He's somewhat of a burdock leaf connoisseur, in fact, and will talk the ears off anyone foolish enough to raise the subject.

skill.name: Lethal Strike
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

50.name: Basilisk
50.description:
"My malevolent eye destroys all!"
A powerful spirit revered as the king of all serpents. Tales of his petrifying gaze and deadly venom send shudders through any who hear his name. Though his combat abilities are beyond dispute, he's still rather new to the monarch racket, so all eyes are on him to see how he'll fare.

skill.name: Stony Stare
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target, with a {probability} of inflicting Poison.

51.name: White Hare of Inaba
51.description:
"Eeep! I've got a bad feeling about this..."
A rabbit spirit who received the grace of a god. She's convinced the vivid dreams she has whenever she takes a nap are trying to tell her something. Unfortunately, they have an uncanny knack of ending before the most important part, and as a result are totally useless.
[Special Bond] Increases Okuninushi's skill DMG

skill.name: Integer Comparison
skill.description: Increases DMG dealt by 2 allies (melee priority) by {delay1} for a limited time.

changes.old:
"Eeep! I've got a bad feeling about this..."
A rabbit spirit who received the grace of a god. She's convinced the vivid dreams she has whenever she takes a nap are trying to tell her something. Unfortunately, they have an uncanny knack of ending before the most important part, and as a result are totally useless.
[Special Bond] Increases {#MonsterName#361}'s skill DMG
changes.new:
"Eeep! I've got a bad feeling about this..."
A rabbit spirit who received the grace of a god. She's convinced the vivid dreams she has whenever she takes a nap are trying to tell her something. Unfortunately, they have an uncanny knack of ending before the most important part, and as a result are totally useless.
[Special Bond] Increases Okuninushi's skill DMG

52.name: Yuki Onna
52.description:
"Are you okay? You're not too cold?"
A spirit the very opposite of frosty in her dealings with others. This sweet-natured snow spirit will go to extraordinary lengths to make those she warms to comfortable. Partial to the odd cheek-reddening tipple, she also has a tiresome habit of speaking in groan-tastic puns when excited.

skill.name: Snowy Investigation
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 3 enemies (melee priority), with a {probability} of inflicting Freeze.

abilities.name: Frosty Spirit
abilities.description: Normal attacks have 9% chances of inflicting Freeze.

53.name: Azukiarai
53.description:
"Spick and span! I can almost see my face in these!"
An inveterate neat-freak with a specialty in azuki bean washing. The to-die-for taste of her washed beans has won her widespread adulation, but she doesn't work as much as you might think—early spring and late fall are her bean-washing seasons of choice.

skill.name: Scrape 'n' Polish
skill.description: Increases DMG dealt by the ally with highest ATK by {delay1} for a limited time.

54.name: Diamond Cutter
54.description:
"Nothing survives my all-powerful cleave!"
A straight-laced, no-nonsense spirit with a deep hatred of anything that isn't 180 degrees. She cuts straight to the chase in all she does, and to heck with any rough edges that get shaved off along the way.

skill.name: Diamond Storm
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 random enemies.

55.name: Gennyo
55.description:
"Nothing can beat my tactical nous!"
The goddess of all things tactical and strategic. The plans she devises are models of military accuracy, right down to the tiniest detail. The only snag? She's never around to see them succeed, as she tends to spend the night before nursing an acute case of "pre-battle runs"... Still, the tactics are flawless, so let's forget that last bit.

skill.name: Operation "Codename F"
skill.description: Reduces all enemies' DEF by {delay1} for a limited time.

56.name: Mizuchi
56.description:
"My dad's Yinglong! I bet he's way awesomer than your dad!"
This young whippersnapper dreams of growing up to be like his old man, the rain dragon Yinglong. He's true to his heritage and got the attitude down pat—unfortunately, his young age means he's naive to a fault, and is all too easily trickable as a result.

skill.name: Young Dragon's Sigh
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the most HP. Target deals {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

57.name: Goblerna
57.description:
"Bow down to my almighty fists!"
"Small-fry" spirit no. 2, as made famous by classic RPG tradition the world over. In keeping with her small-fry status, her job is to be a thorn in the side of any hero at the outset of their journey. She's also a passionate practitioner of martial arts.
[Special Bond] Increases DMG dealt by Gobrute.

skill.name: Mauler's Maelstrom
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

58.name: Shuriken
58.description:
"Target sighted. I shall conduct myself with honor."
The Anima of a throwing star that once belonged to an esteemed martial artist. As far as this fellow's concerned, the mission is all that matters. A true ninja with an unflinching sense of duty, he'll see the job through to completion no matter what dangers lie in store.

skill.name: Airborne Annihilation
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to a random enemy.

59.name: Willy Wisp
59.description:
"Tee hee! You should've seen the look on your face!"
This flickering mischief-maker can often found atop Japan's cliffs practicing her favorite pastime of spooking passersby. Thankfully, her antics have yet to result in serious injury, but everyone's agreed she's a pest all the same. Frequently features prominently at the Bureau of the Occult's rogues gallery.

skill.name: Fires of Grievance
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to a random enemy. Target deals {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

60.name: Nereid: Proto
60.description:
"Cooey-coo! Hello! Could you help a gal apply a spot of lotion to her back?"
Sea-dwelling goddess, and member of a band of mermaids known as the Nereids. In addition to wielding waves with her wile, she also launches fearsome psychic attacks with sweet ditties. She can't hold a note for toffee, however, and is often made fun of by friends and foes alike.

skill.name: Forbidden Melody
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 3 enemies with the least HP.

61.name: Takemitsu
61.description:
"Don't you worry! My blade is as firm as rock!"
An Anima that served at her young master's side through thick and thin before he became a much-feared general. To hear this spirit tell it, her dedication, rousing rhetoric, and strength in adversity were all crucial influences on her young master during his formative years.

skill.name: Master Wielder
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

62.name: Slingshot
62.description:
"Last one to hit the target's a rotten egg!"
Y-shaped propeller of pebbles, and symbol of many a misspent youth. He fancies himself the daring leader of a neighborhood band of vigilantes, but it's mostly all in his head. His undeniable passion tends to inspire more affection than ridicule, however, and most people find him rather sweet.

skill.name: Eye of the Tiger
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the most HP.

63.name: Restless Ghost
63.description:
"Oh, stop being such a snivel baby!"
The spirit of a young girl who died before making her mark on the world. Legend has it her final act was single-handedly stopping six trucks in a valiant effort to save a defenseless kitty from a flattened feline fate. True or not, it's certainly done wonders for her street cred.

skill.name: Sola Punch
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

64.name: Aya Waka
64.description:
"Did you like my dance?"
The childhood self of Fujiwara no Yorinaga. His cherubic looks are said to have won over more hearts than there are stars, as well as paving the road for the intoxicating influence he would enjoy over others in later life.

skill.name: Yorinaga's Purge
skill.description: The 3 enemies with the highest ATK deal {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

65.name: Aka "Red" Chochin
65.description:
"Who're you callin' a lightweight!"
The Anima of a lantern that hangs above a nighttime street vendor. Dab-handed at pulling in both regulars and first-timers, she's also known to be partial to a drink or two (or three) herself... She often wakes up with no memory of the night before, so how she remembers regulars' faces is anyone's guess.

skill.name: Crimson Ambience
skill.description: Increases DMG dealt by all allies by {delay1} for a limited time.

66.name: Kukri
66.description:
"Underestimate me at your own peril!"
The Anima of a short sword once used to perform festive rites. The stunning pattern on her finely curved blade is every sword enthusiast's dream. Some say she once even trounced an army of 400 ruffians single-handedly...

skill.name: Kukri Kombo
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

67.name: Commodore Perry
67.description:
"I'm baaaack!"
Captain of the famous black-painted American naval vessels that were the first to visit Japan's shores. A dyed-in-the-wool Japanophile, he's been making the journey even more regularly since becoming A spirit. The locals used to call him a demon, a title he's taken to with strange enthusiasm—he rarely even leaves home without his comedy horn headband these days.

skill.name: Full Fleet Fusillade
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Pioneer Spirit
abilities.description: Reduces 10% of Max HP and increases 35% skill DMG.

68.name: Pipe Fox
68.description:
"I've got eyes in the back of my head."
A testy fox spirit known for bringing fortune both good and bad. His proficiency with information- and enemy-scouring magic has made him quite the invaluable informant, while his ample fighting skills give his brand that extra-added boost.

skill.name: Iizuna Foxtrot
skill.description: Increases all allies' DEF by {delay1} for a limited time.

69.name: Sun Shangxiang
69.description:
"You want this too, huh?"
Princess of Wu during Ancient China's Three Kingdoms period. Every bit as prodigious a talent as her elder brothers, and an exceptional fighter. Though her marriage to Liu Bei—a suitor thirty years her senior—was one of political convenience, the two forged an instant connection, and could often be seen exchanging peach manju together.

skill.name: Hundred Blooming Blades
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

70.name: Poison S. Brew
70.description:
"What am I drinking, you ask? Why, that'd be telling."
A rare spirit said to produce rice wine with the mysterious ability to weaken demons. Rumor has it the sake itself isn't what's magical, so much as the magic with which this skillful vintner imbues the mix. She's said to be particularly effective at expunging spells. Oh, and the "S" in her name stands for "sake."

skill.name: Alcohol Poisoning
skill.description: A {probability} of inflicting Virulent Poison on all enemies.

abilities.name: Nectar of the Gods
abilities.description: Increases 10% of all allies' Crit DMG.

71.name: Titania
71.description:
"Pretty clothes make everything better!"
This beautiful fairy queen is crazy about fashion, and chooses her outfits for maximum compliment-receiving potential. Unsurprisingly, she lacks much in the way of inner confidence, and secretly worries that her passion for fashion might be a sign of some deeper-seated desire for approval.

skill.name: Kaleidoscopic Beauty
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 3 enemies (ranged priority).

abilities.name: Faerie Queen
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG dealt by Phantasma team members when this daemon is Team Leader.

72.name: Breaking Wheel
72.description:
"What is your crime?"
The Anima of a particularly gruesome method of torture. She might look like an angel sent from above, but don't be fooled—she's got spite in spades, and has doled out despair to sinners, innocents, and the repentant alike in their droves. The wheels scarcely protecting her modesty are said to spin of their own accord.

skill.name: Incandescent Howl
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to surrounding enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun to targets.

abilities.name: Death Deliverer
abilities.description: Increases 15% of DMG dealt.

abilities.name: Ceaseless Pain
abilities.description: All melee foes take 5% more DMG.

73.name: Dojigiri Yasutsuna
73.description:
"Heads up!"
Legendary blade that beheaded ruler of demons Shuten Doji. Despite being feared by demons far and wide, Yasutsuna has an unlikely fan in Shuten Doji himself, who was drawn to her bloodlust to end his time as A spirit. Their bad blood forgotten, the two have since developed a deep connection, though some say that Yasutsuna is a sucker for her former enemy's capacity to empathize with the less fortunate.

skill.name: Destruct Mode
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to nearby enemies.

abilities.name: Demon Dicer
abilities.description: Increases 8% of Crit Rate.

abilities.name: The Five Swords under Heaven
abilities.description: Increases 15% of DMG dealt when one of the Five Swords under Heaven is on the team.

74.name: Konohana Sakuya
74.description:
"How can I get my sister to like me?"
Goddess of childbirth and rearing from Japanese folklore, and younger sister of Princess Iwanaga. A picture of dignity and grace, this classy lady's abundant charm inspires seething jealousy in her elder sister, who harbors a bitter, one-sided grudge against her younger sibling. Desperate to salvage their relationship, Sakuya is currently accepting ideas on how to win her mean sister's affections.

skill.name: Raining Petals
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to 2 allies with the lowest percentage of HP. Targets receive {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Prosperous Goddess
abilities.description: Increases 7% of battle reward drop rate.

75.name: Tokarev Pistol
75.description:
"Me? A split personality? Get outta town!"
This Anima of a perfectly preserved pistol is no stranger to frontline action. She might look sweet, but with a weapon in her hand this girl puts the "miss" in "missile." Although lacking official training, she's a master in military affairs, and can go head to head with multiple trained soldiers and emerge with nary a scratch. Her only weak point is her slight lack in the stature department.

skill.name: Perfect Headshot
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to an enemy (healers priority).

76.name: Komodo Dragon
76.description:
"Step away from the gecko if you value your life."
This lizard spirit's fangs can deliver quite the venomous bite. He harbors nothing but hatred for poachers, and has made it his life's mission to hamper the hunting hordes who'd do harm to his fellow scaly friends.

skill.name: Serpent Charmer
skill.description: Increases Crit Rate to 3 allies (ranged priority) by {delay1} for a limited time.

77.name: Hanzo's Uniform
77.description:
"Can I help you? To DIE, perhaps?"
The Anima of attire once worn by legendary ninja Hattori Hanzo. A Hanzo fanatic who imitates every aspect of her idol, from the way he talks right down to his ticks and habits.
[Special Bond] Increases “Hattori Hanzo” max HP

skill.name: Secrets of the Shinobi
skill.description: Increases the Crit Rate of the ally with the highest ATK by {delay1} for a limited time.

changes.old:
"Can I help you? To DIE, perhaps?"
The Anima of attire once worn by legendary ninja Hattori Hanzo. A Hanzo fanatic who imitates every aspect of her idol, from the way he talks right down to his ticks and habits.
[Special Bond] Increases “{#MonsterName#391}” max HP
changes.new:
"Can I help you? To DIE, perhaps?"
The Anima of attire once worn by legendary ninja Hattori Hanzo. A Hanzo fanatic who imitates every aspect of her idol, from the way he talks right down to his ticks and habits.
[Special Bond] Increases “Hattori Hanzo” max HP

78.name: Helium Elf
78.description:
"But I'm the one trying the hardest!"
An elven spirit sprung from a chemical element. A member of popular EDM (elf dance music) outfit ELF 118. Despite her best efforts, she's often considered the least memorable of her bandmates. Unfortunately, her bland outfits and negligible stage presence mean she'll likely be remaining in their shadows for sometime...

skill.name: Danse Macabre
skill.description: Decreases DMG taken by the 2 allies with the lowest percentage of HP by {delay1} for a limited time.

79.name: Night Trickster
79.description:
"You're up next!"
A headless-horse riding prankster who spends her nights prowling for new victims to scare. The sight of her target's shocked expression is enough to send her on her way, although the trauma stays with her victims long afterward. Rumor has it she spreads stories of her own sightings in an effort to increase her ghostly notoriety.

skill.name: Sadistic Set-Up
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to a random enemy.

80.name: Tonfa
80.description:
"Prepare to fight me!"
The Anima of an ancient Okinawan martial arts weapon. As gifted a brawler as her pedigree suggests, she's especially savvy when it comes to matters of self defense. After traveling all the way to Tokyo expecting some crooks to clobber, she's somewhat dismayed to find less to subdue than she'd originally thought.

skill.name: Twin Dragons
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

81.name: Lily Amaryllis
81.description:
"All I can do is pray..."
The spirit of a hurricane lily recognizable for her red bulbs atop a leafless stem. Her beauty straddles the line between stunning and violent, lending her appearance a heavenly or hellish bent, depending on the mindset of the beholder. Either interpretation suits her just fine as she stands stock still, serene and at one with her surroundings.

skill.name: Funeral Bouquet
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target, with a {probability} of inflicting Weak Poison.

82.name: Rayne Shower
82.description:
"Nnnggh... Come on, RAIN! Just a drop?!"
An as-yet lowly apprentice among other rain-controlling spirits. Although she can just about make it shower with enough concentration, she's yet to achieve a sustained downfall. In thrall to her deluge-dealing, flood-flinging, torrent-tossing heroes, she spends her days mustering up every last droplet she can.

skill.name: Piercing Raindrops
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

83.name: Mummy's Bandage
83.description:
"Currently seeking new mummy for wrapping and good times."
This Anima of a bandage was once wrapped around the mummy of a reclusive senior priest. After witnessing her former host achieve a state of nirvana, she decided she probably didn't have what it takes to follow in his footsteps.

skill.name: Total Bind
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target; decreases target's speed by {delay1} for a limited time.

84.name: Socrates
84.description:
"The world is full of perplexing mysteries. Take my wife, for example..."
The granddaddy of all Ancient Greek philosophers. A renowned polymath and thinker ahead of his time, Socrates made himself none-too-popular when he dared attempt to prove the Oracle of Apollo wrong. He didn't blame anyone else for his predicament, though—he had the foresight to know that would only get him in deeper trouble.

skill.name: Murmurs of Wisdom
skill.description: Reduces all enemies' DEF by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Supreme Sage
abilities.description: Increases 3% of all allies' Crit Rate.

abilities.name: Socratic Method
abilities.description: Restores 25% HP to the 2 allies with the lowest percentage of HP at the start of each wave.

85.name: Kiyo
85.description:
"Do you have any plans later?"
An amorous princess with a constant eye out for potential suitors. For some reason, she turned into a great serpent after getting burned one too many times in love. She becomes paralyzed if her love interest shows even a hint of returning her deep and torrid emotions, and tends to enjoy wallowing in a misery of her own making.

skill.name: Turbulent Passion
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority).

86.name: Red Hare
86.description:
"No one shall approach me. Even shadows will feel my wrath!"
War-hardened steed of Lü Bu, the villain in beloved Chinese epic "Romance of Three Kingdoms." His flaming mane invokes images of fiery sutures scorched into ravaged battlefields. Even as a spirit, he reserves his saddle exclusively for Lü Bu, and refuses to be "broken in" by anyone else.

skill.name: Crimson Afterglow
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the row of enemies directly in front.

87.name: Gryphon
87.description:
"Steal my gold, will ya?! I'd like to see ya try..."
A legendary figure from numerous stories of lore, and the living embodiment of arrogance. He's a mixture of kings both furry and fowl, for which reason he's often considered a go-to symbol of royalty. Of course, Mr. Bighead here just assumes it's because he's so darn popular.

skill.name: Swipe From the Blue
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

abilities.name: Guardian of Gold
abilities.description: Increases 10% of the number of soulstones received from battle.

88.name: Diamond
88.description:
"Even if the heavens forgive you, I shall not!"
The hardest of all natural materials known to man. Possessed of a gritty will deserving of her namesake, this young swordfighter's legendary blade fires rainbow beams to cleave through her foes. Despite her tough facade, her noble soul is said to be fragile like glass. Take care you don't break her... or let her break you.

skill.name: Prism Slicer
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the row of enemies directly in front.

abilities.name: Unbendable Will
abilities.description: When HP is 1/3 or less, Reduces 60% of DMG taken.

89.name: Mephistopheles
89.description:
"That's right, have no fear! I have your back, after all..."
Grants the wish of any who make a deal with him in exchange for their eternal soul. No one knows for sure what goes through his head most the time, but it's probably something to do with collecting on hapless victims's debt and dragging them kicking and screaming into the underworld.

skill.name: The Price of Kindness
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the most HP, with a {probability} of inflicting Virulent Poison.

abilities.name: Demonic Lure
abilities.description: Normal attacks have a 28% of inflicting Poison.

abilities.name: Faust's Pact
abilities.description: Absorbs a 15% of DMG dealt as HP.

90.name: Himiko
90.description:
"Calm yourself! Who do you think you're talking to? (Yeah, that sounded queenly! Go me!)"
The spirit of a shaman queen who ruled Yamataikoku long ago. Her shamanic powers were strong and she used them to save her domain many times. That's how she went from being one of many shrine maidens to being the queen. She actually enjoyed being a shrine maiden, but her serious side wouldn't permit her to turn down the offer to rule the land, so she's trying to start acting more like a queen. She unexpectedly finds it very fulfilling and is completely satisfied with her new role.

skill.name: Unmistakable Oracle
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 3 enemies with the highest ATK, with a {probability} of inflicting Silence.

abilities.name: Shrine Maiden
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG dealt.

abilities.name: Queen of Yamato
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG dealt by Divina team members when this daemon is Team Leader.

91.name: Kuji Kanesada
91.description:
"Your life is worthless if you don't constantly try to improve yourself!"
The spirit of a Tao sword with the number 9 carved into it. It's not only super sharp but also has incredible anti-monster powers due to the 9 carved into it. He has complete confidence in his own abilities and can't stand people who are all talk and no walk. He sharpens his senses everyday with intense training and drills. And if you greet him in a half-hearted tone, you'll start throwing up blood. The word on the street is that he is much softer when dealing with ambitious people who want to get ahead in life.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: Refined Blade of Virtue
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

abilities.name: Japanese Magic Knight
abilities.description: Skill attacks have 24% chances of inflicting Stun.

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

92.name: Hariti
92.description:
"I am a Buddhist guardian deity, after all."
The spirit of a guardian goddess of Buddhism. As the goddess of safe childbirth and childrearing, she is something of a mother figure. But when she gets angry she turns into a yaksha and chases people around, so no one wants to make her mad. She doesn't want children to see her in yaksha form, either. People who do anger her can at least savor the feeling of pure fear.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: Second Coming of the Yaksha
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (melee priority).

abilities.name: Mother of All
abilities.description: Restores 15% HP to the ally with the lowest percentage of HP at the start of each wave.

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

93.name: Zhuge Ling
93.description:
"I'm just as much a genius as my brother!"
The spirit of the sister of a famous military tactician from the Three Kingdoms period in Chinese history. She has a complex about the fact that her name didn't go down in history even though she worked just as hard as her brother and is just as smart. Since becoming a spirit, she's been doing everything she can to make a name for herself.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: Razor-sharp Wit
skill.description: Increases DMG taken by 2 random enemies by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Genius Tactician
abilities.description: Increases 10% of all allies' Crit DMG.

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

94.name: Scarlett Shott
94.description:
"I'm not good for much besides archery..."
The spirit of a hero's beloved bow from Chinese mythology. The bow was involved in the legendary shooting down of nine suns. She is a nice, mild-mannered girl in addition to being an expert with the bow, but she's a bit weak-spirited and often finds herself in trouble. All this trouble has made her a bit of a wise woman in worldly matters, though. She's scared of crows and runs to hide whenever she sees one and waits for it to go away. When asked why, she said seeing crows gives her flashbacks to when she had to shoot down the nine sunbirds.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: Sure Shot
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority).

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

95.name: Gilles de Rais
95.description:
"Who dares to belittle the talent of a French commander?"
The spirit of a commander considered to be a hero and savior of France. He's best known for the bad things he did while alive, so lots of people get the wrong idea and avoid him at all costs. However, he regrets what he did in the past and is searching for a way to make up for it. He has the strength you'd expect from a hero and savior. He's always concerned about the well-being of Joan of Arc, viewing her like a younger sister. He can't seem to get along with a certain archangel for certain reasons.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: Rallying Cry
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

96.name: Amitabha Tathagata
96.description:
"Trust in me, and I'll lend you my power."
The spirit of a bronze plate from the Heian Period with an image of the Buddha carved into it. Far from being an enlightened bodhisattva, she loves being the center of attention. And it's gotten even worse ever since she was declared a national treasure. She does have deep faith and undeniable strength, so lots of people really trust in her.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: All-seeing Eye of Buddha
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to all allies and cures them of Poison.

abilities.name: Amitabha Power
abilities.description: Immune to Poison.

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

97.name: Mikhael
97.description:
"May I interest you in a divine revelation?"
The spirit of an archangel considered the greatest angel of them all. She takes actions for the good out of her faith in God, but things don't always work out the way she plans. This bothers her a lot, and sometimes things end up even worse than when they started. Still, she continues to reign supreme as an archangel thanks to her unparalleled effort and faith.
[Event] Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

skill.name: Saved by Revelation
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to 3 allies (melee priority). Targets receive {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Archangel
abilities.description: Restores 4% HP to all allies at the start of each wave.

from_description.event_name: Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!

98.name: Uesugi Kenshin
98.description:
"This battle is mine."
The spirit of a daimyo from the Warring States Period who was known as the god of war. She can easily beat foes even when she's outnumbered, so her battles never end in a draw. She's blessed with both beauty and strength. Uesugi Kenshin presented as male when he was alive, but due to extenuating circumstances, he took on a female form as a spirit.

skill.name: Godly Pressure
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Warm-hearted Warlord
abilities.description: Increases 15% of DMG dealt when Takeda Shingen is on the team.

abilities.name: God of War
abilities.description: All melee allies take 5% less DMG and deal 5% more DMG.

99.name: Cerberus
99.description:
"Transforming to Cerberus mode!"
A chimera with a puppet based on Cerberus, the watchdog of the underworld. Her personality changes based on the puppet that she's using, so things can get pretty crazy with the right combination. After making some kids cry, she's not allowed to perform for them anymore.
[Special Bond] Increases “Orthrus [Festival]”’s skill DMG

skill.name: Underworld Comedy
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target; decreases target's speed by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Three Beasts, One Body
abilities.description: Increases 15% of Crit Rate when Chimera and Hydra are all on the team

changes.old:
"Transforming to Cerberus mode!"
A chimera with a puppet based on Cerberus, the watchdog of the underworld. Her personality changes based on the puppet that she's using, so things can get pretty crazy with the right combination. After making some kids cry, she's not allowed to perform for them anymore.
