727.name: Stella: Perseus
727.description:
"I am a man who has been born to be a hero! "
A spirit transformed from one of the Ptolemy 48 constellations. A young swordsman who is passionate about heroes of mythologies. Being one of Zeus' illegitimate sons, he is gifted with exceptional talents. On top of his impressive competence with both the sword and magic, his incredible "luck" is simply beyond the scope of reason. It is such an incredible attribute so much so that no matter how badly he screws up, he will somehow end up succeeding in the end. In other words, it's simply OP. His half-sister Athena seems to be terribly fond of him too, and she never seems to be able to reject his requests... Although he is very much in love with his fiancee Andromeda, she was on the record for saying "I will never marry someone who hasn't achieved significant accomplishments." As such, he is currently in the process of feverishly training himself.

skill.name: Star Slicer
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Heroic Wish
abilities.description: Increases own level by 15.

728.name: King Enma
728.description:
"While desire is not equivalent to evil, it does become a problem if you let it consume you. "
A spirit transformed from the king of the netherworld who passes judgment to the deceased based on the deeds they have performed when they were alive. He is strict, almost to the point of being neurotic, and as long as something catches his attention, he will never rest until he figures it out. Despite often being made fun of by his friends as a troublemaker, he is perfectly suited for his position as the judge of hell. He is on great terms with Satan and Hades, who have agreed to divide the vast territories of hell and rule their turfs separately in peace. He treats and loves Satan like his own daughter but recently he hasn't seen too much of her because she made new friends. Seeing the happy expression on Satan's face gives him mixed feelings of joy and loneliness...

skill.name: Judgment of Inferno Demon
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Flames of Dignity
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

abilities.name: Judge of the Netherworld
abilities.description: Increases 10% of Crit DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

729.name: Nektar
729.description:
"Do not let your work and labor build up!　It's best if you finish whatever you need to do today! "
A spirit transformed from the ambrosia that means "honey" in Greek mythology. Contrary to her delicate and exquisite appearance, she is in fact a professional and efficient secretary to Zeus. She often picks up or cleans up the mess that Zeus leaves behind. Despite her habit of offering sound advice to Zeus who is willful and unrestrained in his ways, she respects him more than anyone else and feels deeply honored to be able to work for him. Zeus is well aware of this fact and has therefore been taking advantage of her by leaving all his work to her. When she realized the gravity of the situation, she reported to Hera and that had led to terrible consequences.

skill.name: Golden Drop
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to ally with the lowest percentage of HP. Targets receive {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Drink of the Gods
abilities.description: Restores 50% HP to the ally with the lowest percentage of HP at the start of each wave.

730.name: Guo Jia Fengxiao
730.description:
"As long as I am around, you should give up any idea of pulling any tricks behind my back. "
A spirit transformed from the famed tactician who served Cao Cao. He was the renowned strategist who helped his master in many military campaigns with impressive stratagems and creative ideas but sadly passed away at a young age due to illness. His untimely demise was mourned by many. It is said that the outcome of the battle at the Red Cliff would have been very different if he were still alive at the time. Cao Cao placed a great deal of trust in him. On the other hand, he is terribly lazy and negligent in his personal life, which is a side of him that no one should ever learn from. He hasn't changed his ways after becoming a spirit and has often found excuses to go out and have fun. And he would always get reprimanded by Xiahou Dun when his cover gets blown...

skill.name: Vaulting at Wuhuan
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Wei's Tactician
abilities.description: Increases 20% of skill DMG dealt by Divina team members at the start of the final wave.

731.name: Wild Star Thorn
731.description:
"The life of every living organism begins from nothingness and ends in nothingness… Why don't you return to Mother's embrace as well…"
The embodiment of miasma that came from outer space. "One who devours everything and in the end will consume even himself. "A spirit that heralds the doom for the universe. The true essence of miasma is actually the highly concentrated form of desires of life. By fulfilling the wish and impulses of the spirit that has assimilated the miasma, it grows ever stronger and will eventually become "an entity that embodies all" that devours all spirits in order to become the ultimate life form. When it reached the solar system, it was separated from its emotional half of "Malefic Being: Thorn" when he fought Zeus. He has thus been waiting for the perfect opportunity to strike again. However when Sola and company stopped his wicked plan, he was consumed along with the miasma that "Malefic Being: Thorn" assimilated and came back as the ultimate life form. He continues to assimilate all forms of energy and grows ever larger. And his rampage will only end when he has consumed everything.
[Event] Guild Conquest

skill.name: Destruction for You
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 3 enemies with the highest ATK, decreases targets' speed by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: The Dragon of Avarice
abilities.description: Increases 30% of Crit Rate and increases 10% of battle reward drop rate.

732.name: Muramasa [3rd anniversary]
732.description:
"Your path……must be created with your own strength nyan! !"
A spirit transformed from a renowned blade with many legends and stories. During her involvement in the incident with Sola and company, she gained the ability to control powers that are directly opposite to her own and evolved into "Divine Blade." The experiences also enabled her spirit to grow and mature. Her confidence and unwavering belief in herself became the source of her strengths. The fact that she is capable of striking at an opponent's weak spot at any time alone already makes her a formidable opponent; yet her most deadly power lies in her command of the hybrid force of divinity and demons to execute an "Absolute Cleave." There is nothing in existence that can withstand her slash. Apparently it is akin to gambling with your life if you ever point a cat teaser in her general direction.
[Event] Clavicle of the King

skill.name: Flash of Divinity and Demon
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority).

abilities.description: Increases 15% of skill DMG to Anima team members at the start of each wave.

733.name: Okita Soji [3rd anniversary]
733.description:
"I shall wager my everything with this move!"
A spirit transformed from the Captain of the 1st unit of Shinsengumi's - which was a faction of swordsmen who protected Kyoto during the Bakumatsu Era. After his infusion with the soul of Okita Soji, he awakened the true power that laid dormant in his body and attained the level of "God of Sword." With his newly awakened power of "Temporal Jump," he can circumvent the process of "cutting" and directly go to the result of "slashing his opponent." The speed of his sword flash is beyond imagination. Not only that, his movements have also become as smooth and seamless as the flow of water; he can easily parry any attacks made against him and unless one has attained the state of seeing with his/her mind's eye, his/her attack wouldn't even be able to find its target. Nevertheless, his infusion also exacerbated his illness and now he can only fight at his full power for no longer than 3 minutes. But even so, it is said that there are less than five individuals in this world who can last for longer than a minute in a fight against him... Still, he is training just as diligently as ever on a daily basis, and perhaps that's what makes him "a genius at diligent training".
[Event] Clavicle of the King

skill.name: Ultimate Secret Sword ─ Empty Death─
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the highest ATK.

abilities.name: God of Sword

734.name: Ibaraki Doji [3rd anniversary]
734.description:
"I can definitely do better than this! This will not stop me in my path!"
A spirit transformed from the capable lieutenant of Shuten Doji. He is also said to be the incarnation of the Demon General who will be the next leader of all demons. Because of his passion for railways and the profound sentiments of camaraderie with his companions, he was able to evolve into "Demon God" - gaining incredible powers that make him an equal to Shuten Doji. In addition to that, due to the numerous campaigns and missions he took part, his talents and competence as a commander finally bloomed as he attained the ability of "Conqueror" - a talent that augments the strength of his troops by multifold when under his command. Although he still has a penchant for easily getting carried away and fond of women, he has recently learned to behave himself when Hoshikuma Doji gets the upper hand... Although the two have denied having feelings for one another, one really can't help feeling that they act and behave as if they have been couples for an extremely long time...
[Event] Clavicle of the King

skill.name: Kishingeki ─ Rain of May─
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Conqueror
abilities.description: Increases 25% of Crit Rate by Phantasma team members when this daemon is Team Leader.

abilities.name: Kishin
abilities.description: Increases 15% of skill DMG of Phantasma team members at the start of each wave.

735.name: Charon
735.description:
"I don't really care for any of those trivial things, as long as you pay up."
A spirit transformed from the famous boatman who ferries souls of the dead across Styx and answers to Hades directly. As far as she is concerned, anything in the Underworld can be solved with money. As long as one can afford her fees, no principles or guidelines will apply to her. She is a professional navigator who gets the job done. She charges on an hourly basis and she accepts various payments including rokumonsen, one obol or electronic currency. When asked about her infatuation with money, her response was: "Because my dream is to one day travel around the world." As inspiring as her goal is, given the ten of thousands of dead who go to the Underworld each day, will she actually be able to take such a long leave? And by the way, she is an old friend of Orpheus. Once she ditched her job just because she wanted to hear him play his harp and she was severely reprimanded by Hades as a result.
[Event] Clavicle of the King

skill.name: Sanzu River
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun.

abilities.name: Guide of the Underworld
abilities.description: Increases 25% of the number of soulstones received from battle.

736.name: Meito Kotetsu [3rd anniversary]
736.description:
"Why waste time thinking when you just don't have the brain power for the job?"
A spirit transformed from the finest even among the best katanas that have been recognized as Saijo Owazamono. Frivolous and cocky by nature, he has a bad habit of getting out of control whenever he gets excited. He is very close to his partner Kondo Isami and nothing is taboo between the two. Sometimes Isami would catch a glimpse of him feeling down for having said something over the top... Even so, he is deeply trusted by Isami, who was on the record for saying, "It is all thanks to Kotetsu that I was able to get out of the Ikedaya incident unscathed." On a related note, he and Kashuu Kiyomitsu and others have been old acquaintances and the true reason that Isami emerged from the incident without injury was because they got careless. And as such, he feels slightly awkward in their presence.
[Event] Clavicle of the King

skill.name: The Killing Blow
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 3 enemies (ranged priority).

abilities.name: Katana of Might
abilities.description: Reduces 10% of DMG taken and Increases DMG dealt by 20% at the same time.

737.name: Pipe Fox [3rd anniversary]
737.description:
"Well if it is a request from you, I guess I have got to take it seriously."
A spirit transformed from the tricky fox demon who commands both the powers of good and ill fortune. Apt at gathering intel, you can count on his to always have the latest intelligence. He is very close with the Sakuma Clan. Despite being thought by everyone to possess enormous power, he would easily give up a fight even against a much weaker opponent as he doesn't think it's worth the effort. Consequently, he has been overly underestimated in this world. But he doesn't seem to care about what others feel about his and he has gone on the record for saying, "I'd rather be treated with contempt by the weak if that saves me from having to show the ace in my sleeve." And thus, no one has actually witness his power.
[Event] Clavicle of the King

738.name: Cao Cao [3rd anniversary]
738.description:
"Make your choice; serve me, or die……"
A spirit transformed from the legendary warlord, politician and hero who has left the world with incredible literary works as his legacy. The true leader of the Clavicle of the King; he is the mastermind who wishes to free spirits from the control of mankind. To achieve his ambition, he has spent years in meticulous planning and preparation. In fact, even the past encounters he has had were simply part of his stratagem. He was the cruel and merciless tyrant who once love mankind more than anyone else but ended up being responsible for the deaths of most men in history. Just what exactly he sees through his dark, burning pupils ...nobody will ever know.
[Event] Clavicle of the King

skill.name: Blade of Ruinous Seven Stars

abilities.name: Mastermind

739.name: Tsuchimikado Mikado [Demon]
739.description:
"Alright, pull yourself together already!"
The Director of the Bureau of the Occult and the young mistress of the Tsuchimikado Clan. Borrowing the power of Senji Ryakketsu, she merged with Shuten Doji and become the ultimate entity - a "joker" that commands power beyond the comprehension of human wisdom. Born with the most powerful spirit essence ever gifted to heirs of the Tsuchimikado Clan, she led a secluded life from the mortal world and grew up with spirits and demons instead. As a result, she has grown to see spirits and demons as equals to mankind. Because of this, she secretly developed a method of manifestation that is unrestricted by karma and named her technique as "Karmic Liberation" - giving life to numerous spirits who could live in freedom. Her greatest wish is to create a world where humans, spirits and demons can live in peace, harmony and joy. Nevertheless, for spirit agents who use and order demons as tools and soldiers, her ideas are nothing short of radical and out of the box. Will the concept and vision of a world of inclusion and harmony be accepted by mankind? The answer is still out there.
[Event] Clavicle of the King

skill.name: Sword of Protection/Blade of Annihilation
skill.description: Increases the DMG of 2 allies with the highest ATK by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Karmic Liberation

abilities.name: Director of the Bureau of the Occult
abilities.description: Increases skill DMG of all team members by 45% when this daemon is Team Leader.

740.name: Shuten Doji [3rd anniversary]
740.description:
"It's been so long since my last fight. Don't blame me if I have forgotten how to pull my punches."
A spirit transformed from the most powerful entity that is the leader figure for all spirits and demons in Japan. He was once the mighty demon that brought terror unto this world from his lair at Mount Oe. However, he was put into an extended slumber due to Minamoto no Yorimitsu's clever ambush. When he manifested in the modern days, his terrible grudge drove him to exact his revenge on mankind but was utterly humbled by Tsuchimikado Mikado as he finally tasted defeat. Just as he thought he would be put to a long slumber, he was surprised by the fact that Mikado had not sealed him away and instead chose to befriend him. This period of placid serenity helped him to find peace within his heart. Even though he can't find it in himself to show his true feelings in the presence of Mikado, he is extremely loyal to her and will even willingly give up his life for her sake. And it is thanks to Mikado that he managed to see heart to heart with Dojigiri Yasutsuna, his once sworn enemy...

skill.name: Psalm of Destructive Sin
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to enemy with highest ATK, target receives {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Deputy Director of the Bureau of the Occult
abilities.description: Increases 25% of skill DMG of the 2 allies with highest ATK.

abilities.name: Demon King
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG of Phantasma team members at the start of each wave.

741.name: Senji Ryakketsu
741.description:
"What's this? How did that adorable little darling ended up being such an old hag……"
A spirit transformed from the oldest tome of divination in Japan that has been passed down as a family heirloom in the Tsuchimikado Clan. With the spirit of Abe no Seimei residing in the tome, she has been taking care of Mikado ever since she was a little girl and reverted to her true form as a tome when she matured. She is one of the very few spirits that truly understands the inner workings of the world through techniques of divination and the truth behind the existence of spirits. Despite appearing to be a loquacious individual who has trouble keeping her mouth shut, she is actually cunningly diverting the subject with useless trivial talks so that she never has to impart what really matters. In other words, she achieves her silence through ceaselessly talking. No one has greater confidence in Mikado's potentials and strengths than her and whenever Mikado finds herself in crisis, she would break her seal and manifest in the world.

skill.name: Qimen Dunjia Formation
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to ally with the highest ATK. Targets deal {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.description: Reduces 15% of DMG taken of all team members; increases 20% of ATK speed at the start of the final wave.

abilities.name: Da Liu Ren
abilities.description: Increases 43% of crit rate and increases 100% of crit DMG of skill targets at the same time.

742.name: Ame-no-Uzume [3rd anniversary]
742.description:
"Here's a song for you to keep you entertained!"
A spirit transformed from the goddess of dance and performance in Japanese mythology. She is the oldest dancer in the history of Japan and it is said that all who see her dance would become captivated by her performance. According to rumor, her latest goal is to become an idol who can sing as well as she can dance but apparently her progress in singing has not improved by the slightest. Only heaven knows if the day she becomes an idol would ever come. She is also one of the best friends of Cherry Blossom Front from the same agency. But as flowers don't bloom in the Underworld, Cherry Blossom Front would be entirely useless, and thus she has taken Cherry Blossom Front's place in this incident. And lastly, she is still on bad terms with Goddess Amaterasu...

skill.name: Song of Angel
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Goddess of Performance
abilities.description: Increases 10% of the EXP gained from battle and increases 10% of battle reward drop rate.(only take effect once to the team)

743.name: Kaguya [Tsuki Hime]
743.description:
"Hohoho!　How did you like that? Very sexy right?"
This is the true form of the spirit transformed from the princess of the moon when she unleashes her true powers. When her stores of lunar energy reach the maximum, she will be able to maintain this form for 5 minutes. Her true identity is an extraterrestrial demon lord who has been banished to this dimension to atone for her sins. She has the ability to manipulate gravity; she doesn't age and will never die. However, such powers are sealed off completely when she is in the form of a child. If she really wishes to, she could easily turn Earth into a black hole without breaking a sweat. But now that she has befriended other spirits, she no longer finds it in herself to do such a thing. A demon lord who cannot stand to be alone due to fear of solitude has apparently gone out to play with her friends today, as usual.

skill.name: Gravitational Disintegration
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Extraterrestrial Princess
abilities.description: Increases 35% of Skill DMG and 35% of Crit DMG.

744.name: Sabionari
744.description:
"Complacency rots the soul……and I'll never want that to happen to me."
A spirit transformed from the priceless acoustic guitar made by the renowned luthier Antonio Stradivari. She is the guitarist of unparalleled renown in the genre of spirit music. She used to be a lady from an extremely affluent family. But as she loathes a lifestyle of material comfort without challenges and hardship, she grabbed a guitar and simply left home, without any knowledge of the world. As she led a life of a street performer who can barely put food on her table, she encountered Homer, who shares similar values and beliefs with her. The two have been partners ever since. It is said that their neighbors would hear the sounds of guitar duet from the run-down apartment they once dwelled from time to time and such stories have become legends... Not only that, she actually jammed with a saucepan once but the session ended up in a fight due to differences in their perceived musicality. She will probably never accept any offer for ensemble or group performance from now on.

skill.name: Resonating Eradication
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies; decreases targets' speed by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Legendary Instrument
abilities.description: Increases 15% of DMG of all allies at the start of each wave.

745.name: Carmilla
745.description:
"Come, let the roses of blood bloom."
A spirit transformed the beautiful princess and one of the true ancestors of vampires. She is the chief of the 108 clans of vampires with the lineage of true ancestors - an energetic girl who is most trusted by Count Dracula. Despite being a vampire, she is not affected by sunlight in anyway and can withstand direct exposure. Apparently she has used it as an excuse to go about all sorts of places to have fun using the excuse of going on missions. Not only that, since food in modern times are much richer in nutritional values, she apparently no longer has to drink blood for sustenance. But even so, one will find his life force secretly drained away if he ever gets careless. One should never let his/her guard down just because of her appearance as a bishojo. On a related note, her ability is "Bloody Create." It allows her to manipulate the iron in her blood to create all sorts of weapons and devices of torture as she wishes.

skill.name: Bloody Spiral
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 2 enemies with the least HP. Targets take {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Beautiful Princess of True Ancestor
abilities.description: Increases own level by 15.

746.name: Chrysanthemum the Ninja
746.description:
"Let me show you my secret techniques that men will never be able to imitate!"
A spirit transformed from a female jonin -a leader of all female ninjas. She is the mentor of Camellia and Peony and has been nicknamed as "The Dark Hunter" while serving as the Captain of the Exorcist Squad. Apart from her exceptional fighting techniques and her cool head, her "charisma" is the deadliest weapon in her arsenal. Just as her opponents become bewitched by her sensual charms, she would take them out with a sudden attack that came from nowhere. Consequently, male spirits have grown to develop a genuine fear of her ……Apparently she has been rather upset about the ineptitude of dames who do not know how to leverage their gifts as women.

skill.name: Ran‧Kachofugetsu
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Huntress of the Dark
abilities.description: Increases 50% of Skill DMG at the start of the final wave.

747.name: Yagyu no Odachi
747.description:
"You have to defeat me first before you can claim to be the strongest!"
A spirit transformed from the famed odachi that has been passed down as a family heirloom; a great weapon that runs more than two meters in length. Anyone who is deemed worthy of wielding her must have proven his/her mettle as the true heir and master of the Yagyu Shinkage-ryu. As she embodies the honor of a prestigious martial family with profound history, she is well-mannered and gracious in her demeanors. But due to her absolute confidence in her own abilities and strengths, she would inadvertently perceive others in a condescending manner...The truth is, she is a dame who knows little of the ways of the world and whenever she gets called out on this fact, she would become infuriated. In fact, this whole incident wouldn't have happened if this wasn't brought up in conversation when she went on a blind date... She really has tons of energy as a young lady, that's for certain. On a side note, she almost had no experience in dealing with other famed swords and katanas. The only friend she gets along well is Kuji Kanesada, whom she often spars with.
[Event] Guild Conquest

skill.name: Edge of Destruction
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Legacy of Yagyu Shinkage-ryu
abilities.description: Skill attacks increase 40% DMG taken by targets.

748.name: New Year Sunrise
748.description:
"Please look upon me all you like!"
A ghost only visible on New Year's Day, and widely believed to be extremely valuable. Bowing down before her beauty is said to ensure peace and tranquility for the year ahead. But, actually, contrary to popular belief, she's always wandering around here and there. It's just that no one takes any notice of her until New Year's Day. She's a pretty lonely ghost for the rest of the year, and craves more attention.

749.name: Nyx
749.description:
"I'll paint the sky black so that everyone can sleep peacefully."
Original form. One of Greek mythology's original deities, and the goddess of night. She lives together with her good friend Hemera, the goddess of day.

750.name: Snow Sprite
750.description:
"Hey, you! Come and play with me! You want a snowball fight? Mind if I use icicles? Tee hee... How about we build a snowman? Yippee!"
A child spirit who appears in snowy territories. The family of any who play with her are said to be blessed with good fortune for generations to come.

751.name: Obi Ceremony
751.description:
"You look like you've never tied an obi before!"
A spirit who embodies the traditional Japanese ceremony where a seven-year old girl puts on her first obi sash. She is rather precocious, believing herself to be an expert on all things sash-related, and she likes to lord it over less enlightened children. It is true that girls are often more mature than boys at that age, but considering herself a full-blown grown-up might be taking things too far.

752.name: Hakama Ceremony
752.description:
"Ready, set, jump!"
A spirit who embodies the traditional Japanese ceremony where a five-year old boy dons his first hakama robe. Believing that his ceremony was getting overlooked in favor of all the other events in the Shichi-Go-San Children's Festival, he became determined to raise its profile. He's willing to do anything to get people to acknowledge the supreme importance of the hakama ceremony - even stepping on his close friends' toes. He usually apologizes for this afterwards, though.

753.name: Jack of Hearts
753.description:
"I would lay down my life in service of my Queen."
A dashing swordsman who serves the Queen of Hearts. Blessed with a heroic disposition and admirably egalitarian in his treatment of others, he's rather popular with the ladies. His background is somewhat shrouded in mystery, but that's a story for another time.

skill.name: Blinding Flash
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Queen's Knight
abilities.description: All Divina team members deal 25% more DMG.(only take effect once to the team)

754.name: Kotofurunushi
754.description:
"Does the sound of the koto harp not cause your chest to swell?"
The Anima of a koto harp, who plays beautiful music. Her music heals those who listen to it, and she plays dutifully every day.

skill.name: Elegant Melody
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to all allies. Targets deal {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Centennial Tune
abilities.description: All Anima team members take 5% less DMG

abilities.name: Healing Opus
abilities.description: Restores 5% HP to Anima team members at the start of each wave.

755.name: Arko
755.description:
"Name your target and I'll shoot it right down!"
The soul of Oberon's bow. The arrows fired from this magic-infused bow have never once failed to strike their target, but he only ever listens to what Oberon tells him to do.

skill.name: Bullseye
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Faerie King's Magic Bow
abilities.description: Increases Combat Damage by 30%.

abilities.name: Oberon's Decree
abilities.description: Increases Attack Speed by 50% when 'Oberon' is present.

2182.name: Circus Elephant
2182.description:
"It's all about the circus! Anything else is irrelephant!"
The ghost of a well-trained circus elephant. She tends to make bad elephant jokes, especially when she gets excited. She's a bit clumsy, too, and steps on a few toes now and then.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Thousand-Ton Press
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Elephantine Strength
abilities.description: Deals 22% more DMG.

2183.name: Human Cannon
2183.description:
"Here we gooooooooo!"
The ghost of a cannon that fires human cannonballs. A spring is used to propel the person into the air, as gunpowder explodes for effect. She says that, with enough force, a human can be shot across an entire continent, but her claim remains unverified.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Zero-Range Fire
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Gunpowder Boost
abilities.description: Increases 6% of ATK speed of all allies.(only take effect once to the team)

2188.name: Chikamatsu Monzaemon
2188.description:
"What a glorious stage!"
The ghost of the great dramatist of Japanese joruri puppet theater and kabuki plays. He heard of a new and unusual form of entertainment called the circus, and, full of curiosity, rushed to see it. He was so greatly impressed with the dynamic flamboyance of the show that he left before it was over to start work on his next creation.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Love Suicide
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Playwright Master
abilities.description: Increases 38% of skill DMG.

2184.name: Zeami Motokiyo
2184.description:
"A circus, eh? Hmm. Interesting."
When the ghost of this great Noh theater playwright and actor heard of this particular form of entertainment for the masses, she rushed to see it. She was especially impressed with the circus clowns, and was apparently inspired by the stark white and bright red of their makeup.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Fūshikaden
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Silence.

abilities.name: Yūgen Beauty
abilities.description: Reduces 4% of DMG dealt by all foes at the start of each wave.

2187.name: Lion Clown [Wild]
2187.description:
"Roooooooar!"
The ghost of a lion tamed by Harlequin. People originally thought that it was Löwe the Clown who had mastery over the beast, but it was always really Harlequin who was in control. It just goes to show what a truly skillful lion tamer Harlequin is.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Riot
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to nearby enemies.

abilities.name: Beast's Instinct
abilities.description: When HP is 1/2 or less, Increases 42% of DMG dealt.

2193.name: Trick Pony
2193.description:
"Did you ever see a stunt like this?"
The ghost of a circus pony whose specialty is stunt-riding tricks. She and her rider are so in tune that there's never a slip-up no matter what tricky pose the rider attempts. She is devoted to practicing, and is fairly humble to boot. When it comes to the day of a show, however, she can become quite nervous and get a little out of control. But that's when her hours of practice kick in, and she always manages to give a flawless performance.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Phantom Ride
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Perfect Stunt
abilities.description: Skill attacks increase target's ATK speed by 42%.

2194.name: Beast Tamer
2194.description:
"Someday... I'll do it someday...!"
A tamer of fierce animals, she is one of the newer members of the circus troupe. Her ability is undisputed, but she tends to be overshadowed by Löwe the Clown, and secretly considers her a rival. Perhaps this sort of competitive rivalry is really what's behind all of the circus troupe's successes?

skill.name: Wildebeest Migration
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies. Targets take {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Competitive Spirit
abilities.description: All Phantasma team members deal 5% more DMG.

2195.name: Circus Trapeze
2195.description:
"Wheeeee!"
The Anima of a flying circus trapeze. Her breathtaking flights through the air are a featured attraction of the circus. But, truth be told, breakneak speeds are a little outside of her comfort zone, and she often feels quite nervous.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Jet Swing
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Flying Trapeze
abilities.description: Increases 25% of ATK speed.

2189.name: Löwe the Clown
2189.description:
"Welcome to our great show!"
The new ringmaster of a circus company that travels all over the world. At first, she felt burdened by her new role, but after a certain incident, she experienced personal growth and began to embrace her destiny. Many believe that, at this rate, she may even surpass the great Harlequin one day.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Beast Menace
skill.description: Increases DMG dealt by all allies by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: New Ringmaster
abilities.description: Increases 18% of max HP of all allies.

2185.name: Harlequin
2185.description:
"I'm looking forward to seeing the circus of this new era!"
The ghost of the ringmaster of a circus company that travels all over the world. Earlier in her career, she was an unparalleled clown and lion tamer and a brilliant performer in her own right. She led her circus troupe for many years, but then finally stepped down after finding a talented successor.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Beast Clutches
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to 2 allies with the highest ATK, increases {delay1} crit rate to target for a limited time.

abilities.name: Ringmaster's Dignity
abilities.description: Reduces 35% the DMG taken by skill targets.

abilities.name: Lion Tamer
abilities.description: Increases 35% of Crit DMG by the 2 allies with the highest ATK.

2186.name: Il Milione [Circus]
2186.description:
"I have lots more tales to tell of the Far East!"
The ghost of a book detailing the adventures of a famed explorer in the Orient. On a subsequent trip to the Far East, he ran into a circus troupe and observed their performance. He is now apparently planning to write a new book with exaggerated tales of what he witnessed. Unfortunately, there still seems to be plenty of gullible folks willing to believe his every word.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Very Tall Tale
skill.description: Increases Crit Rate to all allies by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Land of Gold
abilities.description: Increases 20% of skill DMG of all anima allies.

abilities.name: Strange Tales
abilities.description: At the start of the final wave, all foes take 25% more damage.

2190.name: Russet Helm
2190.description:
"Tut, tut. What ever are we going to do with that ringmaster?"
The ghost of a red grizzly. Her name comes from her hair, which gives her the appearance of wearing a red battle helm. She is one of the longest-serving members of the circus company, and acts as a sort of adviser to the troupe.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Great Bear
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Veteran's Wisdom
abilities.description: Increases 10% of skill DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

abilities.name: Red Armor
abilities.description: Increases 15% of Max HP.

2192.name: Maeda Toshimasu [Circus]
2192.description:
"Ah! You see? This is why I can never give this life up!"
An eccentric character who can often be found trawling red-light districts. When he caught wind that an outrageously flamboyant show was coming to town, he was so excited he couldn't sleep. Completely enthralled by the circus, he even went around in a clown costume for a while.
[Event] Greatest Show On Earth

skill.name: Show Time
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Kabukimono
abilities.description: Increases 20% of Crit Rate.

abilities.name: Best in Sengoku
abilities.description: Increases 15% of DMG dealt.

2191.name: Ring of Fire
2191.description:
"Let it burn!"
The Anima of a blazing circle of fire. She's ordinarily quite fiery and hot-blooded, even to the point of being somewhat overbearing, but when her flames subside, her passion bottoms out, too. Some would even say she suffers from bipolar mood swings.

skill.name: Scorching Moonring
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 3 enemies (ranged priority), with a {probability} of inflicting Burn.

abilities.name: Fiery Heart
abilities.description: Increases 25% of DMG dealt by Anima team members at the start of the final wave.(only take effect once to the team)

2196.name: Cat Sith [Circus]
2196.description:
"You know, I think this world suits me just fine!"
A cat sprite originally from Scotland. Always a lover of pranks, jokes and japes, the fact that circus performers actually get paid for this stuff has come as a revelation to her. Rumors that she has cut some kind of secret deal with the circus troupe remain unconfirmed.

skill.name: Feline Feat
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Nine Lives
abilities.description: Increases 50% of Crit DMG.

2373.name: Harvest Moon
2373.description:
"Everyone, stop staring at me! You're making me blush!
The spirit of the magnificent full moon that appears from the 15th to 16th of the 8th month of the lunisolar calendar. She gives off an aura so enchanting no one caught in its glow can look away from her spellbinding glory. But if you look too long, you will inevitably recognize your own insignificance in this universe, forcing you to reconsider your own existence.

skill.name: Full Moon Energy
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to all allies. Targets deal {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Moon's Blessing
abilities.description: Increases 45% of DMG of the 2 Phantasma team members with highest ATK.

abilities.name: Existential Crisis
abilities.description: Increases 4% of max HP of Phantasma team members at the start of each wave.

2374.name: Moon Viewing Pickpocket
2374.description:
"I'll take that, thank you very much!"
This spirit of a dumpling-stealing bandit always appears around the time of autumnal moon viewing in Japan. For the record, she is actually quite welcome to steal on this night, as it is the one time it is permitted for anyone to help themselves to dumplings. It's a tradition that anyone is allowed to pretend they're stealing, you know, just for fun. So if you're looking for crime and drama at a public event, she may let you down. If you do spot her, feel free to give a playful "Lock up your valuables, everyone," but there's no need to call the police.

skill.name: Dumpling Swiper
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 2 enemies with the highest ATK.

abilities.name: Traditional Theft
abilities.description: Skill attacks have a 100% of inflicting Stun.

abilities.name: Swift Moves
abilities.description: At the start of the final wave, enemy with the most HP takes 35% more damage.

2377.name: Mooncake
2377.description:
"I'll put you in a calorie coma!"
The spirit of a Far Eastern treat. She has a sweet tooth, and is particularly generous of heart. She can't help but think the greatest gift is the gift of oneself, so you're likely to find her distributing large quantities of mooncake. She has been known to bake bombs into the cakes as a prank, so double check before taking a bite. Don't eat too many. They're rather calorific.

skill.name: Calorific Terror
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 enemies (ranged priority), with a {probability} of inflicting Burn.

abilities.name: Generous Gift
abilities.description: Restores 9% HP to the ally with the lowest percentage of HP at the start of each wave.

2376.name: Tannia
2376.description:
"Nobody harvests 'em like I do!"
A spirit who gathers taro potatoes for the moon viewing. If the harvest yield is high enough around the night of the 15th, she offers up the harvested taro to the moon at a harvest festival. She counts among her friends chestnuts and beans.

skill.name: Taro Entrée
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Harvest Festival
abilities.description: Increases 20% of skill DMG.

1318.name: Mino
1318.description:
"I await the return of the mighty one!"
A hardcore online gamer who got sucked into cyberspace. Mino is his online nickname, and he's a warrior belonging to the "Grilled Meat Gobblers" Guild.

skill.name: Upscale
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Online Gamer
abilities.description: Increases 30% of Crit DMG.

1319.name: Little Witch
1319.description:
"This is my moment! I'm finally going to be top of the class!"
A trainee witch. She may be something of a klutz, but she boasts impressive magical abilities. She was born lucky and can turn any setback into a success.

skill.name: Witch's Draught
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Born Lucky
abilities.description: Increases 20% of Crit Rate.

1320.name: Kotetsu [HW]
1320.description:
"Oi, ... Stop staring at me like that! You're making me uncomfortable..."
The soul of the beloved inscribed sword of Isami Kondo, head of the Shinsengumi special police force. On the orders of the Shinsengumi, she is wearing a Halloween costume. She's very reserved and somewhat lacking in grace, but is lovable all the same.

skill.name: Fiery Spirit
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Sword of the Shinsengumi
abilities.description: All allies deal 3% more DMG.

1301.name: Stewart [HW]
1301.description:
"Now then... Shall I teach you the proper way to roast a pumpkin?"
The soul of a steward android developed by a scientist. The memories of all Stewart models are part of a network, enabling them to be continually updated with the latest data.

skill.name: Silver Sliver
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Perfect Service
abilities.description: All allies take 3% less DMG.

1304.name: Goddess of Misfortune [HW]
1304.description:
"This outfit suits me, wouldn't you say? I'd be happy to dress like this for a while."
It's said that all who come into contact with this goddess will be struck by disaster. She has come all the way to the Halloween Tower to meet you.

skill.name: Evil Destiny
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Impending Doom
abilities.description: Reduces 4% of DMG dealt by all foes at the start of each wave.

1305.name: Goddess of Poverty [HW]
1305.description:
"Tee hee hee! It's so nice to be here with you!"
It's said that all who come into contact with this goddess will be plagued by poverty. She has come all the way to the Halloween Tower to meet you.

skill.name: Good Fortune
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Plagued by Poverty
abilities.description: Normal attack targets have 33% chances of increasing 15% more DMG taken.

1312.name: Yottie [HW]
1312.description:
"Who's for a Halloween cruise? If you don't join, I'll play a trick on you!"
The soul of a cruiser. She has decided to dress up especially for you. She's just waiting to sail away with you on an autumnal cruise.

skill.name: Hook, Line, Sinker
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 3 enemies with the highest ATK.

abilities.name: Autumn Cruise
abilities.description: Decreases 15% of the ATK speed of all foes at the start of each wave.

abilities.name: Yacht Party
abilities.description: Increases 15% of skill DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

1308.name: Amber [HW]
1308.description:
"I feel so happy and blessed! My life is like a dream come true!"
The soul of an automated doll made by the genius doll-maker, Abel. She is Doll No. 3 in the hard-to-come-by Five Fragrances Series. Musk twisted her arm and got her to come to the Halloween Tower.

skill.name: Amber Concentrate
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the enemy with the most HP. Targets deal {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Five Scents Doll
abilities.description: Reduces 40% of DMG taken at the start of the final wave.

abilities.name: Heart of a Doll
abilities.description: Increases 10% of Crit DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

1311.name: Grim Reaper [HW]
1311.description:
"Now you are free of all ties and bonds..."
A goddess with dominion over death itself. She is one of the Three Goddesses of Trouble, along with the Goddesses of Poverty and Misfortune. She is feared as the bringer of death, but she also symbolizes rebirth and new beginnings.

skill.name: Final Judgment
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to enemy with highest ATK, target receives {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Death's Hand
abilities.description: Increases 60% of skill DMG.

abilities.name: Three Great Calamity Gods
abilities.description: Increases 15% of Max HP and Reduces 20% of DMG taken.

1317.name: Jack-O-Lantern
1317.description:
"With me, it's trick or treat all year round!"
It wouldn't be Halloween without this little one. She is the Anima of a pumpkin lantern. She loves to eat and hates to be left alone. Now she's come to see you and is hoping for some Halloween candy.

skill.name: Jack-O-Lantern
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Burn.

abilities.name: Symbol of Halloween
abilities.description: All Anima team members take 10% less DMG

abilities.name: Tsukumogami
abilities.description: Increases 15% of skill DMG to Anima team members at the start of each wave.

1314.name: Titania [HW]
1314.description:
"Halloween is so much fun! I can't wait to tell the folks in the forest all about it! "
The Queen of the Fairies who reigns over the other sylvan sprites. The late-night Halloween event took her fancy, so she came all the way to Japan to take part. She forced her way into the Halloween Tower especially to see you.

skill.name: A Queen's Blessing
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies.

abilities.name: Fairy Queen
abilities.description: Increases 15% of skill DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

abilities.name: Forest's Protection
abilities.description: Increases 15% of Crit Rate at the start of each wave.

1310.name: Cat Sith [HW]
1310.description:
"I'm sleepy. Do you mind if I curl up on your lap?"
A cat sprite originally from Scotland. She loves pranks, jokes, and japes. She and her best buddy Cu Sith are inseparable.

skill.name: Catcall
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Mischievous Heart
abilities.description: Increases 15% of max HP of Phantasma team members.

abilities.name: Best Friends Forever
abilities.description: Increases 35% of DMG dealt by Phantasma team members at the start of the final wave.

1307.name: Cu Sith [HW]
1307.description:
"If you and Cat Sith are happy, then so am I!"
A dog sprite that originates in Scotland. "Cu" is a Celtic term for "dog". She is best friends with Cat Sith. She was responsible for organizing the Halloween Tower event.

skill.name: Hair-Raising Howl
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to all enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun.

abilities.name: Loyal Partner
abilities.description: Increases 10% of Crit Rate by all Phantasma team members at the start of every wave.

1323.name: Hare of Inaba [HW]
1323.description:
"There's no better time to play all manner of tricks!"
The white hare that appears in the Izumo myth of ancient Japan, she is also a goddess who has had a temple built in her honor. She loves nothing better than playing tricks on people, so she wasn't going to miss Halloween.

skill.name: Divine Hymn
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to 2 allies with the lowest percentage of HP and cures them of all negative status effects.

abilities.name: God of Pranks
abilities.description: Increases 15% of the EXP gained from battle.

1309.name: Musk [HW]
1309.description:
"I feel like I'm dreaming whenever I'm with you... Stay and dream with me forever..."
The soul of an automated doll made by the genius doll-maker, Abel. She is Doll No. 2 in the hard-to-come-by Five Fragrances Series. She got Vanilla to make her Halloween costume for her.

skill.name: Musk Concentrate
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to enemy with highest ATK, target receives {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Five Scents Doll
abilities.description: Increases Crit DMG by 90% when 'Amber' is present.

abilities.name: Enchanting Scent
abilities.description: Increases 60% of DMG dealt at the start of the final wave.

1321.name: Ameno Uzume [HW]
1321.description:
"Halloween's a great excuse for a party... I'm really getting into the mood!"
A goddess with extraordinary artistic talents. She heard there was a party going on, so decided to dress up and take a look for herself.

skill.name: War Dance
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to 3 allies with the highest ATK. Targets deal {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Goddess of the Arts
abilities.description: Increases the ATK speed of all divina allies by 25%.

abilities.name: Party Fever
abilities.description: Increases 40% of DMG dealt by the 2 allies with the highest ATK.

1303.name: Rat Clan: Koko [HW]
1303.description:
"Hold still... This might sting a bit."
A rat spirit that has developed the ability to transform. Rat Clan: Koko After conducting a straw poll among Rat Clan members at their HQ, Club-Q, she decided to go with a nurse outfit for Halloween.

skill.name: Phantom Sigh
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 2 random enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Weak Poison.

abilities.name: Club Q
abilities.description: Reduces 10% of DMG taken.

1306.name: Rat Clan Boss [HW]
1306.description:
"Nothing can stop us if we stick together!"
A rat spirit that has developed the ability to transform. The leader of the Rat Clan. He boasts formidable powers, but now that he's risen to the top, he can relax and show his more light-hearted side.

skill.name: Phantasm
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Leader's Dignity
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG of all Phantasma allies.

1302.name: Rat Clan Henchman [HW]
1302.description:
"You know you can rely on the Rat Clan!"
A rat spirit that has developed the ability to transform. The Rat Clan always stick together, and have recently begun to venture beyond their home turf.

skill.name: Bluff
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Strength in Numbers
abilities.description: Increases 10% of Crit rate.

1313.name: Halloween Tower
1313.description:
"I'm so happy to see your smiling faces!"
The soul of the Tower, she only appears at Halloween. An ally of Cu Sith and Cat Sith, she is a generous soul who is willing to go to the ends of the earth to cheer people up. She wants nothing more than to make you happy.

skill.name: Under Siege
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Generous Spirit
abilities.description: Restores 25% HP to all allies at the start of each wave.

1491.name: Kintaro
1491.description:
"Now I can show what I can really do!"
Named as one of Minamoto no Yorimitsu's retainers, known as the Four Heavenly Kings, he was involved in slaying Shuten-doji. As well as a rare strength and a great beauty in which he has unending faith, he is also dutiful and devoted to the people around him, and has a tendency to cry at the drop of a hat. Everyone from Yorimitsu to the other Heavenly Kings dote on him, and regard him as a younger brother figure. As a complete package, though, he has his flaws... Particularly in the brains department...

skill.name: True Spirit
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Four Heavenly Kings
abilities.description: All Divina team members deal 4% more DMG.(only take effect once to the team)

1493.name: Kishimojin[aya]
1493.description:
"Don't worry! I won't eat you so long as you behave yourself."
In her days as a Yasha demon, she stole other people's children in order to feed her own, thought to number over a thousand. After a lot of fuss, she became the goddess of children and easy childbirth. She has still not forgotten the taste of human flesh, however, and her cold eyes never show signs of smiling.

skill.name: Munch
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Blood of the Yasha
abilities.description: Restores 30% HP to the ally with the lowest percentage of HP at the start of each wave.

1496.name: Hive Hunter
1496.description:
"Hey noobs! You're going down!"
A hardcore online gamer, and leader of the Yakiniku Teishoku guild. He is known online by his username Hive Hunter. He ventured into cyberspace searching for powerful monsters for his game. Apparently, he was looking for a monster known only as the Demon.

skill.name: Gamer Spirit
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Yakiniku Teishoku
abilities.description: Increases 10% of DMG dealt; Increases 10% of skill DMG.

1495.name: Sakatokego no Kami
1495.description:
"Come on, just one quick drink. You won't regret it!"
The goddess of making sake, she brews special amenotamu sake for the other gods. Since she doesn't drink alcohol herself, she is always encouraging others to sample her product. The vibrant and aromatic sake she produces is simply without equal. She is very well connected, and is a familiar face in the ghost community.

skill.name: Rush of Energy!
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Amazake
abilities.description: Increases 3% of max HP of Divina team members.

1476.name: Hariti
1476.description:
"Right, you lot!　Are you behaving yourselves?"
She was once a people-eating devil, but changed her ways after coming to understand the pain of losing a loved one. Having understood how wonderful life can be, and the joy that comes of securing that wonder, she began to work as an educator in the demon kingdom.

skill.name: Discipline Time
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Reformation
abilities.description: Restores 5% HP to all allies at the start of each wave.

1497.name: Ibaraki Doji[aya]
1497.description:
"Whatever you desire, my Lady..."
Shoten-doji's most valued lieutenant, and the only demon she trusts. She refers to Shoten-doji as "my Lady," and they appear to be close friends. Some claim they are more than friends, however... She speaks rather roughly when Shoten-doji is not around. She has quite a dry personality, but is certainly evil enough to be considered a demon... She loves desserts.

skill.name: Great Demon's Love
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to 2 allies (melee priority). Targets receive {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Loyal Oni
abilities.description: Reduces 30% of DMG taken when one of “Shuten Doji” is on the team.

1498.name: Dojigiri
1498.description:
"No need to worry when I'm around. I'll silence all those whining brats!"
One of the five heavenly swords. Yoritomo used this sword to decapitate Shoten-doji. It seems the presence of this sword stops children crying at night. She values personal relationships so highly, she believes they are the only thing that cannot be cut.

skill.name: Moonlit Slice
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to enemy with highest ATK, target receives {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Five Great Swords
abilities.description: Increases 50% of DMG dealt when one of the Five Swords under Heaven is on the team.

abilities.name: Oni-Slaying Blade
abilities.description: Increases 50% of Crit Rate.

1489.name: Shuten-doji (Wild)
1489.description:
"Gnnnyyyaaarrrrrrrrgghh!!!"
Japan's most powerful demon, who lives in the Oeyama mountain in old Tanpa province, governing over a pack of several hundred demons, and striking fear into the hearts of those in the neighboring city. It loves a drink and, when it's feeling tipsy, likes to capture young girls, take them home and eat them as snacks. It's an earnest sort, though, and always makes sure to thank those who come to capture him before murdering them. A hardliner, it hates nothing more than half measures.

skill.name: King's Return
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to current target.

abilities.name: Oni of Mt. Oe
abilities.description: Reduces 40% of DMG taken and slowly restores HP over time when HP is 1/2 or below.

1494.name: Goddess of Good Fortune
1494.description:
"Forget about fortune tellers. If I'm around, happiness is guaranteed!"
A goddess who brings good luck to all around her. She is especially fond of money, drinking, and fine clothes, and is usually found hanging around seedy areas where money changes hands, talking about love. She is the nemesis of the Goddess of Poverty.

skill.name: Breeze of Fortune
skill.description: Increases Crit Rate to all allies by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Wealth Abound
abilities.description: Increases 7% all Divina team members' Crit Rate at the start of each wave.

abilities.name: Poverty Begone
abilities.description: Increases 20% of the EXP gained from battle.Increases the number of soulstones received from battle by 30%.

1452.name: Go-Go
1452.description:
"How will you respond to my next move?"
A spirit that visits dedicated players of Go, a traditional Chinese board game. Playing with him will lead to a marked improvement in your game. He has been really looking forward to teaching you the rules.

skill.name: God's Hand
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Opening
abilities.description: All allies deal 3% more DMG.

1453.name: Cloud Mirror
1453.description:
"Gaze upon my surface, and who knows what you'll find! Heh heh!"
The spirit of an ancient mirror, it is said to reflect the true nature of any demon, faerie, or human who looks into it. Not to be confused with your altogether less mysterious companion Mira.

skill.name: Polished Mirror
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to 3 allies with the lowest percentage of HP. Targets receive {delay1} less DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Demon-Quelling Light
abilities.description: Reduces 25% DMG dealt by all foes at the start of the final wave.

abilities.name: Protective Mirror
abilities.description: Reflects 25% of DMG taken back to attacker.

2370.name: Peculiar Raine
2370.description:
"What shall I rain down next?"
If it ever rains anything other than rain, snow, or sleet, this spirit is surely somewhere close by. Any rain that passes through her sphere of influence metamorphoses into fish or spears before raining down to the earth.

skill.name: Spearstorm
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Anomalous Rain
abilities.description: Decreases 20% the ATK speed of all foes.

abilities.name: Raining Fish
abilities.description: Increases 75% of skill DMG.

1490.name: Shuten-doji (Calm)
1490.description:
"Parfait, I said! Bring me parfait!"
Japan's most powerful demon, who lives in the Oeyama mountain in old Tanpa province, governing over a pack of several hundred demons and striking fear into the hearts of those in the neighboring city. She is very partial to drinking, but even more than that, she likes Ibaraki Doji. Of late, she's acquired a taste for parfait as well. She has something of a regal air about her, and remains unflappable. Her important position, she feels, makes it shameful to make her true feelings known.

skill.name: Demonic Ambition
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 2 enemies with the most HP. Target take {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: Oni King's Dignity
abilities.description: Skill attacks have 50% chances of inflicting Virulent Poison.

abilities.name: A Dear Friend's Love
abilities.description: Reduces 30% of DMG taken.

1466.name: Kyobu Tanuki
1466.description: <color=#f4e48e>"With me in tow, that makes 808! Onwards, soldiers!"</color>The spirit of a <color=#ef9843>military general</color> raccoon dog in charge of <color=#ef9843>808 raccoon dog soldiers</color>. It came all the way from Shikoku to join forces with you.

skill.name: Belly Bash
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: 808 Tanuki
abilities.description: Increase 15% of DMG dealt by the 2 allies with the highest ATK.

1465.name: Riya Amagasaki
1465.description:
"Who d'ya think you're calling 'sweetheart'? I'll wipe that smile off your face!"
A wandering warrior who trained in the arts of swordmanship to avenge her father. Currently acting as your bodyguard, she often fights on behalf of those weaker than herself.

skill.name: Vengeance Blade
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to further enemies, with a {probability} of inflicting Stun.

abilities.name: Bodyguard's Spirit
abilities.description: Increases 40% of skill DMG.

1430.name: Poli'ahu [Xmas]
1430.description:
"Stay by my side and I'll make sure you'll get the white Christmas you've been dreaming of!"
A Hawaiian snow goddess. She'll be spending Christmas with you this year, so she's planning a romantic festive season with plenty of snow.

skill.name: Snowdrop
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Goddess of Snow
abilities.description: Absorbs a 15% of DMG dealt as HP.

1431.name: Natalia Nyfe [Xmas]
1431.description:
"You're shivering! ...Aren't I cold, you ask? No... No, for some reason, I'm strangely warm inside..."
The soul of a standard-issue Soviet army knife. She hides it well, but in actual fact she's pretty nervous about her first Christmas spent with you.

skill.name: Holy Night's Offering
skill.description: Reduces all enemies' DEF by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: Pride of the Spetsnaz
abilities.description: All allies take 3% less DMG.

1432.name: Kiku Ichimonji [Xmas]
1432.description:
"Well, what do you think? I've never dressed up like this before, not even for Officer Okita..."
The soul of a sword that was used by Sochi Okita, commander of the first unit of the Shinsengumi police force. Urged on by the others, she's dressed up in a special Christmas outfit to please you.

skill.name: Code of the Shinsengumi
skill.description: Increases the Crit Rate of 2 allies with the highest ATK by {delay1} for a limited time.

abilities.name: First Squad of the Shinsengumi
abilities.description: Increases 10% of Skill DMG and increases 60% of Crit DMG.

1433.name: Hashihime [Xmas]
1433.description:
"We'll still spend wonderful evenings together next year too, right...? And the year after that...? That's a promise, yes?"
A jealous she-devil who kills with her powerful curses. She was the first to perform the cursing ritual known as Ushi no Koku Mairi, in which nails are driven into a straw doll used to represent someone. You'd be best to keep your roaming eye in check this festive season...

skill.name: All-Consuming Envy
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to 3 enemies (ranged priority).

abilities.name: Ushi no Koku Mairi
abilities.description: Increases 17% of skill DMG of the 2 allies with highest ATK.

1434.name: Snow Dome
1434.description:
"How beautiful the snow is! And how much better it would be if I could watch it close beside you..."
The soul of a snow dome depicting a gorgeous snow scene. Each year, she watches the Christmas festivities from within her glass capsule, but what she'd really like is to spend it by her loved one's side...

skill.name: Silent Night
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: World in Glass
abilities.description: At the start of the final wave, enemy with the most HP takes 12% more damage.

1435.name: Santa Claus
1435.description:
"It was destiny to meet you here, on this Holy Night when I distribute my love... My gift to you is me myself. The space beside me belongs to you and you only..."
The one and only Santa Claus, who makes everyone's wishes come true. Outside of Christmas time, though, he lounges all day and night in your bed.

skill.name: Merry Christmas
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 3 enemies with the highest ATK.

abilities.name: Christmas Present
abilities.description: Increases 15% of skill DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

1436.name: Salamander [Xmas]
1436.description:
"Oh! Is this a d-d-date? Aren't you cold? You can share my coat, if you like... Oh, was that the wrong thing to say?"
A fire spirit and one of the Four Elements. In the summer, everyone found her heat too much to bear, but she's secretly pleased that people are keen to cuddle up to her now that it's winter. She came to town to buy presents for you and all the fairies in the forest.

skill.name: Flame Column
skill.description: Restores {value} HP. Target deal {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: The Four Elements
abilities.description: Reduces 25% of DMG taken.

1437.name: Pipe Fox [Xmas]
1437.description:
"My master will be here soon, no doubt... I must ensure that this is a truly enjoyable evening for my favorite agent... "
This fox spirit once served a renowned ghost agent master. It can hardly contain its excitement about the arrival of Santa Claus. Of late, it has cast off its favorite pipe and has taken to snuggling up beside the fire to get warm.

skill.name: Bewitchment
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Fox Spirit's Art
abilities.description: All Phantasma allies take 15% less DMG taken.

abilities.name: Waiting for Presents
abilities.description: Decreases 50% the ATK speed of all foes.

1438.name: Kotetsu [Xmas]
1438.description:
"...It's fine. I'm not uncomfortable. If it pleases you, then that is satisfaction enough for me..."
The soul of the beloved inscribed sword of Isami Kondo, head of the Shinsengumi special police force. She's dressed up in Christmas costume following yet another cosplay request from the Shinsengumi officers. Of late she seems to be rather enjoying it...

skill.name: Fiery Spirit
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to enemy with highest ATK. Target takes {delay1} more DMG for a limited time.

abilities.name: The Commander's Blade
abilities.description: Reduces 25% of DMG dealt by opponent with highest ATK at the start of each wave.

abilities.name: Kondo's Beloved Sword
abilities.description: Increases 20% of DMG dealt at the start of each wave.

1439.name: Behemoth (Calm) [Xmas]
1439.description:
"Oooh... That cake is absolutely delicious... Say, today seems like a great day for us to stick together. What do you say?"
A huge monster that has risen from the underworld. If she gets too worked up she'll turn back into a enormous monster, so you'll need to keep an eye on her. She's something of a celebrity in both the underworld and the heavens, and receives a huge number of Christmas presents, but she claims that spending her time together with you is the best gift of all.

skill.name: Thunderball
skill.description: Deals {value} DMG to the 2 enemies with the highest ATK, with a {probability} of inflicting Freeze.

abilities.name: Demon World Idol
abilities.description: Reduces 20% of DMG taken.

abilities.name: Power of the Behemoth
abilities.description: Absorbs 15% of DMG dealt as HP.

1991.name: Mary Magdalene
1991.description:
"Let us pray. Let us atone for all that has been done in our names."
A veritable saint, she witnessed the resurrection of the one she served. Since then, she has suffered all manner of lies and aspersions cast on her character. She still prays for peace and justice to reign. These prayers ensure that the faith her master taught her never wavers.

skill.name: Glory of Redemption
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: A Saint's Prayer
abilities.description: Increases 25% of skill DMG by Divina team members.

abilities.name: Unwavering Faith
abilities.description: Increases 45% of DMG dealt.

1992.name: Sacred Mimic
1992.description:
"Sorry! I'm not quite what I seem!"
The last ghost anyone wants to encounter at this time of year. She rifles through the stacks of presents delivered by Santa Claus, takes the ones she wants, and replaces them with fake gift boxes with nasty surprises inside. Known by some as the Phantom Thief, she is unmistakably a real pain.

skill.name: Surprise, Surprise
skill.description: Restores {value} HP to ally with the highest ATK, increases {delay1} crit rate to target for a limited time.

abilities.name: Phantom Thief
abilities.description: 50% chances of restoring HP to skill targets by 100%.

abilities.name: Gift Swap
abilities.description: All Phantasma team members deal 30% more DMG.

1993.name: Gift Box
1993.description:
"Take whichever one you like!"
A spirit that was formed from the mountains of presents under Christmas trees around the world. She symbolizes the hopes and dreams of every child. Although she embodies so many things, she takes the form of an individual female ghost. She appears to them in the form that each child desires.

skill.name: Merry Time
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Dreams Come True
abilities.description: Reduces 40% of DMG taken at the start of the final wave.

1994.name: Fir Tree Sprite
1994.description:
"Hee hee hee! I look pretty cute, wouldn't you say?"
A sprite born from a festive fir tree. She loves being draped in flashing lights, and is insanely enthusiastic about anything remotely shiny. If it's gaudy, glitzy or garish, you can rest assured that she's all over it. No one gives her the time of day once January rolls around, so she has to take her chance to show off while she can.

skill.name: Glitzy Lights
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Gorgeous Decorations
abilities.description: Increases 23% of skill DMG dealt by Divina team members at the start of the final wave.

1995.name: Wish-Filled Stocking
1995.description:
"Sorry! I just can't fit any more in!"
A ghost who aims to cater to the expectations of children during the festive season. She's the stand-by of choice in the world of socks. She's folded away, worn by no one, for the whole year, then she comes into her own at Christmas. She loves to really sock it to you by being jam-packed with a jaw-dropping selection of presents. She's the ghost who keeps on giving.

skill.name: Countless Gifts
skill.description: Can be used as bond and in guild conquest.

abilities.name: Full of Goodwill
abilities.description: Restores 3% HP every 5 seconds.

30000.name: Limit Break Orb: supreme
30000.description:
Possesses the ability to tap into latent power.
Filled with a peculiar energy that binds itself to the spirit essence of those who touch it, pushing their power to the next level. Use this orb when enhancing a daemon to Limit Break it.

30004.name: Limit Break Orb: special
30004.description:
Possesses the ability to tap into latent power.
Filled with a peculiar energy that binds itself to the spirit essence of those who touch it, pushing their power to the next level. Use this orb when enhancing a daemon to Limit Break it.

30011.name: Fortune-telling Memory
30011.description:
Memories of the daily divinations of a popular fortune-teller.
This magatama contains the good will that helped passerby avoid misfortune in their lives. It makes Divina type spirits very happy.

30012.name: Priestly Memory
30012.description:
Memories of a deeply pious priest.
His will to lead the downtrodden to the path of righteousness was captured in this magatama, which continues to illuminate the way to goodness. It increases the piety of Divina type spirits.

30013.name: Mysterious Memory
30013.description:
Memories of one who caused many miracles.
The feelings of an angel sent down from heaven are contained within this magatama, and it continues to cause more miracles even now. It fills Divina type spirits with a mysterious power.

30014.name: Shogun's Memory
30014.description:
Memories of a shogun who led many military campaigns.
People adored his gallantry, and his wishes to create a peaceful world have lain inside this magatama ever since then. It gives a strong wish for peace to Divina type spirits.

30015.name: Tyrannical Memory
30015.description:
Memories of a tyrant who ruled the world.
This magatama contains the tyrant's attitude toward life, including the boldness it required. It gives Divina type spirits the power needed to control the world.

30021.name: Impish Memory
30021.description:
Various cute pranks pulled by an imp...
This magatama contains memories of them all. It makes Phantasma type spirits very happy.

30022.name: Demonic Memory
30022.description:
A demon's countless evil deeds...
This magatama contains memories of how they were performed. It increases Phantasma type spirits's knowledge of evil.

30023.name: Destructive Memory
30023.description:
Memories of a demon that longed for the destruction of the world.
Hatred born from sadness is contained in this magatama, and it burns strong to this day. It makes Phantasma type spirits feel the same way and increases their power.

30024.name: Fiendish Memory
30024.description:
Memories of a demon infamous for bringing about disaster.
The demon's brutality etched fear into the minds of many, and that terrifying power is contained in this magatama. It gives the capacity for brutality to Phantasma type spirits.

30025.name: Demon King's Memory
30025.description:
Memories of one who reigned supreme over all other demons.
This magatama contains great power and constantly emits a strange light. It fills Phantasma type spirits with the demon king's strength and gives them enormous power.

30031.name: Universal Memory
30031.description:
Memories of a beloved treasure.
Though the item itself was nothing special it was treated with great tenderness, and those feelings of happiness are gathered in this magatama. It makes Anima type spirits very happy.

30032.name: Famous Knight's Memory
30032.description:
Memories of a sword carried by an adventuring knight.
This magatama contains concern for the safety of one's new master. It fills Anima type spirits with the strength to protect others.

30033.name: Tender Memory
30033.description:
Memories of a favorite sword carried by a talented knight.
The sword vowed to protect its owner, and those strong feelings are contained in this magatama. It bestows Anima type spirits with the desire to protect their master.

30034.name: Holy Sword Memory
30034.description:
Memories of a sword said to be able to exorcise evil.
It became the favorite sword of a famous knight, and together they cut their way through many a battle. This magatama contains those memories, strong as ever. It gives Anima type spirits kindness and strength.

30035.name: War God's Memory
30035.description:
Memories of a sword carried around as a lucky charm by a knight who was considered a god of war.
This magatama contains memories of protecting the knight even after battle had ended. It gives endless power to Anima type spirits.

30041.name: Soulstone Ticket: Minor
30041.description:
A ticket from the Bureau of the Occult with a picture of a soulstone on it, given to those who have made minor achievements.

"Collected, you can exchange these to get soulstones. I hand them out all day, so come back when you're ready for more."

30042.name: Soulstone Ticket: Middling
30042.description:
A ticket from the Bureau of the Occult with a picture of a soulstone on it, given to those who have made middling achievements.

"Exchange this for a handful of soulstones. If you want more, then keep your nose to the grindstone."

30043.name: Soulstone Ticket: Moderate
30043.description:
A ticket from the Bureau of the Occult with a picture of a soulstone on it, given to those who have made moderate achievements.

"This will get you quite a few soulstones. You deserve it for all the hard work you've been putting in lately."

30044.name: Soulstone Ticket: Major
30044.description:
A ticket from the Bureau of the Occult with a picture of a soulstone on it, given to those who have achieved something of major merit.

"These will get you so many soulstones you'll be grinning ear to ear. Trust me, you earned them!"

30045.name: Soulstone Ticket: Max
30045.description:
A ticket from the Bureau of the Occult with a picture of a soulstone on it, given to those who have achieved something of maximum merit.

"One of these will get you more soulstones than you can imagine. I don't hand them out to just anyone, but someone of your caliber more than deserves it."
